1
00:00:23,299 --> 00:00:27,268
[music playing]

2
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:39,315
[SINGING] She says yes.

3
00:00:39,418 --> 00:00:41,765
He says no.

4
00:00:41,869 --> 00:00:43,802
She says goodbye.

5
00:00:43,905 --> 00:00:46,839
Oh, no, baby, please don't go.

6
00:00:46,943 --> 00:00:49,566
Can we stay?

7
00:00:49,670 --> 00:00:57,954
She says OK, if we say what
we mean, and mean what we say.

8
00:00:58,058 --> 00:01:03,201
Oh, baby, just tell
me what you want.

9
00:01:06,238 --> 00:01:15,661
Ooh, baby, tell me
what you need from me.

10
00:01:15,765 --> 00:01:18,147
'Cause we got to
keep on loving life.

11
00:01:21,253 --> 00:01:26,155
Keep it falling,
falling down below.

12
00:01:26,258 --> 00:01:31,056
'Cause where there is
truth, love survives.

13
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:36,579
And in the end, maybe
that's all we need to know.

14
00:01:36,682 --> 00:01:38,581
Come to me.

15
00:01:42,412 --> 00:01:47,141
Please don't deny me, yeah.

16
00:01:47,245 --> 00:01:52,457
'Cause we got to
keep on loving life,

17
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:57,462
keep it from falling,
falling down below.

18
00:01:57,565 --> 00:02:00,568
We've got to keep
our love alive.

19
00:02:03,364 --> 00:02:05,677
Come to me.

20
00:02:05,780 --> 00:02:09,888
I want you to the find me, yeah.

21
00:02:15,687 --> 00:02:19,553
[applause]

22
00:02:19,656 --> 00:02:21,175
Ladies and gentlemen,
from the heart

23
00:02:21,279 --> 00:02:23,867
of Louisiana, all the
way to the Windy City,

24
00:02:23,971 --> 00:02:27,699
my baby cousin, Terry Deveroux.

25
00:02:27,802 --> 00:02:28,562
Not bad, peanut.

26
00:02:28,665 --> 00:02:29,735
You're too kind.

27
00:02:37,916 --> 00:02:38,744
Eric.

28
00:02:38,848 --> 00:02:40,056
Hey, Terry, you were great.

29
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:40,953
Oh, thanks.

30
00:02:41,057 --> 00:02:41,885
I'm glad you could make it.

31
00:02:41,989 --> 00:02:43,749
Can I buy you a
drink or dinner?

32
00:02:43,853 --> 00:02:47,063
Uh, thanks, but it's
late and I'm beat,

33
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,547
and we both got to be up early.

34
00:02:48,651 --> 00:02:49,859
No.

35
00:02:49,962 --> 00:02:51,826
Don't duck me like this.

36
00:02:51,930 --> 00:02:54,035
Now, you owe me
better than that.

37
00:02:54,139 --> 00:02:56,417
Eric, please,
that dog don't hunt.

38
00:02:56,521 --> 00:02:57,591
I don't owe you.

39
00:03:04,356 --> 00:03:05,564
Look, we were friends at work.

40
00:03:05,668 --> 00:03:06,910
We dated some.

41
00:03:07,014 --> 00:03:09,775
It didn't go anywhere, so
we're friends again, I hope.

42
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,777
I don't see it like that.

43
00:03:11,881 --> 00:03:13,952
Well, I wish you
tried to, because that's

44
00:03:14,055 --> 00:03:16,126
the way it's got to be.

45
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:17,300
Look, you're a nice guy, Eric.

46
00:03:17,404 --> 00:03:18,301
I really like you.

47
00:03:18,405 --> 00:03:19,268
I'll see you tomorrow.

48
00:03:25,343 --> 00:03:27,379
HOSPITAL PA: Dr. Keller,
please call your page.

49
00:03:32,142 --> 00:03:33,040
Hey, Eric, these seats free?

50
00:03:33,143 --> 00:03:34,144
Sorry, man.

51
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:35,905
I'm kind of waiting
for somebody.

52
00:03:36,008 --> 00:03:36,802
Oh?

53
00:03:36,906 --> 00:03:39,460
OK.

54
00:03:39,564 --> 00:03:40,875
- What's his problem?
- I don't know.

55
00:03:40,979 --> 00:03:42,256
Needs his space, I guess.

56
00:03:49,746 --> 00:03:50,851
Oh, hang on, you guys.

57
00:03:50,954 --> 00:03:52,577
I'll be right back.

58
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,509
Hey, honey.

59
00:03:53,612 --> 00:03:55,959
Hi, Bill.

60
00:03:56,063 --> 00:03:56,857
You leaving?

61
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,168
Yeah, I got to hurry.

62
00:03:58,272 --> 00:04:00,654
I'm assisting Carter on a
tricky little laparotomy.

63
00:04:00,757 --> 00:04:01,896
Do well.

64
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:02,828
I'll see you tonight.

65
00:04:02,932 --> 00:04:03,829
Yeah.

66
00:04:08,109 --> 00:04:09,525
Take it easy, OK?

67
00:04:09,628 --> 00:04:10,526
Bye.

68
00:04:17,498 --> 00:04:18,913
RENEE: Oh, not again.

69
00:04:19,017 --> 00:04:21,882
You've been robbed?

70
00:04:21,985 --> 00:04:24,333
Yes.

71
00:04:24,436 --> 00:04:27,784
Like I have time
for those lines.

72
00:04:27,888 --> 00:04:28,682
Oh, come on.

73
00:04:28,785 --> 00:04:29,683
They go fast.

74
00:04:33,134 --> 00:04:34,239
It's Renee, right?

75
00:04:34,343 --> 00:04:36,345
Uh huh.

76
00:04:36,448 --> 00:04:38,036
I heard you were
out for a while.

77
00:04:38,139 --> 00:04:40,590
I'm glad to see you back.

78
00:04:40,694 --> 00:04:41,522
Thanks.

79
00:04:41,626 --> 00:04:42,420
Were you sick?

80
00:04:42,523 --> 00:04:44,732
Uh, no.

81
00:04:44,836 --> 00:04:46,389
Actually, I had a miscarriage.

82
00:04:46,493 --> 00:04:49,530
Oh, I'm so sorry to hear that.

83
00:04:49,634 --> 00:04:53,396
I guess I'm just taking
it harder than I thought.

84
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,397
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:54,501 --> 00:04:55,916
I shouldn't be
bothering you with this.

86
00:04:56,019 --> 00:04:58,712
No, no, it's no bother.

87
00:04:58,815 --> 00:05:00,714
You know, you're right
about these lines.

88
00:05:00,817 --> 00:05:02,094
They're ridiculous.

89
00:05:02,198 --> 00:05:03,199
You want to just
sit for a while?

90
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,096
Mhm.

91
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,132
OK.

92
00:05:05,235 --> 00:05:06,685
Excuse me.

93
00:05:06,789 --> 00:05:08,687
Isn't your husband
a resident here?

94
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:11,552
Yeah, Bill's in his last year.

95
00:05:11,656 --> 00:05:14,935
So we thought the
time was right.

96
00:05:15,038 --> 00:05:16,316
I got pregnant on
the first try, and

97
00:05:16,419 --> 00:05:18,835
everything was going so well.

98
00:05:18,939 --> 00:05:20,941
I wasn't very pregnant,
but still, you

99
00:05:21,044 --> 00:05:23,184
wonder, where did that life go?

100
00:05:23,288 --> 00:05:24,703
Don't torture yourself.

101
00:05:24,807 --> 00:05:26,464
That's a mystery
you may never know

102
00:05:26,567 --> 00:05:29,225
the answer to in this life.

103
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:32,435
Personally, I know it's
corny, but I really

104
00:05:32,539 --> 00:05:35,404
believe that everything
happens for a reason.

105
00:05:35,507 --> 00:05:39,097
And one day, we'll
have all the answers.

106
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,513
That was the one and
only real conversation

107
00:05:41,617 --> 00:05:45,034
I ever had with Terry Deveroux.

108
00:05:45,137 --> 00:05:46,587
We didn't know each
other very well.

109
00:05:46,691 --> 00:05:50,039
We worked in different
areas of the hospital.

110
00:05:50,142 --> 00:05:53,111
So when everything
started to happen, I--

111
00:05:53,214 --> 00:05:55,182
I couldn't help but
ask myself, why me?

112
00:06:00,912 --> 00:06:03,880
TERRY: [humming]

113
00:06:16,341 --> 00:06:20,621
[SINGING] Keep it from
falling down below.

114
00:06:20,725 --> 00:06:23,141
[doorbell ringing]

115
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:26,282
Just a second!

116
00:06:30,597 --> 00:06:31,460
Who is it?

117
00:06:39,882 --> 00:06:40,779
Oh, hey.

118
00:06:40,883 --> 00:06:42,056
I wasn't expecting you tonight.

119
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,955
I'm afraid I'm running late.

120
00:06:44,058 --> 00:06:45,819
MAN: Won't take long, Terry.

121
00:06:45,922 --> 00:06:47,579
I'm really in a hurry.

122
00:06:47,683 --> 00:06:48,787
MAN: It'd take five minutes.

123
00:06:52,342 --> 00:06:53,240
I'm singing tonight.

124
00:06:58,797 --> 00:07:00,696
[shouts]

125
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:06,702
[shrieking]

126
00:07:52,817 --> 00:07:53,749
You'll pay for this.

127
00:08:19,913 --> 00:08:20,707
RENEE: Bill?

128
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:22,260
In here.

129
00:08:22,363 --> 00:08:24,262
RENEE: I am so beat.

130
00:08:24,365 --> 00:08:26,195
I don't think I can face
that toxic joint again.

131
00:08:26,298 --> 00:08:27,196
Ta-da.

132
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:31,890
It's so beautiful.

133
00:08:34,962 --> 00:08:35,998
This is nice.

134
00:08:36,101 --> 00:08:37,517
We haven't had a proper
meal together in ages.

135
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:39,139
And I worked my
fingers to the bone.

136
00:08:39,242 --> 00:08:40,623
[laughter]

137
00:08:40,727 --> 00:08:44,109
[suspenseful music]

138
00:08:59,331 --> 00:09:00,988
Oh, how'd it go
with Carter today.

139
00:09:01,092 --> 00:09:02,058
Fantastic.

140
00:09:02,162 --> 00:09:03,957
When I was done
with the procedure,

141
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,166
gave me one of these.

142
00:09:06,269 --> 00:09:07,167
Really?

143
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:08,617
Really, yeah.

144
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,446
Granted, it was a little hard
to see above the mask, but, uh--

145
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,343
Oh, yeah, I bet it was.

146
00:09:11,447 --> 00:09:12,241
He did.

147
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:13,794
I swear he did.

148
00:09:13,898 --> 00:09:16,348
You may just get that
job on the surface.

149
00:09:16,452 --> 00:09:17,867
Maybe I will.

150
00:09:17,971 --> 00:09:20,836
Oh, that guy wants 1,200
bucks to rewire the house.

151
00:09:20,939 --> 00:09:21,871
Bill, we can't afford that.

152
00:09:21,975 --> 00:09:22,803
I know.

153
00:09:22,907 --> 00:09:26,324
[suspenseful music]

154
00:09:43,513 --> 00:09:44,963
[gasps]

155
00:09:46,447 --> 00:09:47,552
You OK?

156
00:09:47,656 --> 00:09:51,176
Uh, I'm-- I'm dizzy.

157
00:09:58,598 --> 00:09:59,944
Better?

158
00:10:00,047 --> 00:10:01,048
Uh huh.

159
00:10:05,535 --> 00:10:09,505
[sirens blaring]

160
00:10:11,472 --> 00:10:14,372
[radio chatter]

161
00:10:14,475 --> 00:10:17,444
[shouting]

162
00:10:22,449 --> 00:10:24,416
FIREMAN: Come on, let's
get to these flames!

163
00:10:30,975 --> 00:10:31,769
FIREMAN: All right.

164
00:10:31,872 --> 00:10:33,287
Stand by with the booster line.

165
00:10:33,391 --> 00:10:34,806
FIREMAN: Get those
people out of here!

166
00:10:54,239 --> 00:10:57,242
You don't-- you don't
smell smoke, do you?

167
00:10:57,346 --> 00:10:58,243
No.

168
00:11:02,696 --> 00:11:03,801
MAN [ON MEGAPHONE]:
The streets need

169
00:11:03,904 --> 00:11:06,389
to be kept clear for
emergency vehicles only.

170
00:11:06,493 --> 00:11:08,322
Anybody in here?

171
00:11:08,426 --> 00:11:10,117
[shouts]

172
00:11:10,221 --> 00:11:11,291
Where'd he go?

173
00:11:11,394 --> 00:11:12,292
I don't know.

174
00:11:16,192 --> 00:11:17,849
Take a look at this.

175
00:11:17,953 --> 00:11:20,852
[siren blares]

176
00:11:41,597 --> 00:11:42,494
OK, what have we got?

177
00:11:42,598 --> 00:11:43,392
Where are we going?

178
00:11:43,495 --> 00:11:44,289
Third floor.

179
00:11:44,393 --> 00:11:45,256
Victim's a white female.

180
00:11:45,359 --> 00:11:46,706
Looks like an arson case.

181
00:12:02,514 --> 00:12:06,035
She's 20, 25 years old.

182
00:12:06,139 --> 00:12:08,728
Just a kid, for God's sakes.

183
00:12:08,831 --> 00:12:10,074
JOE: I want a statement
from the guy who

184
00:12:10,177 --> 00:12:12,697
called in the fire, where
he was when he saw it

185
00:12:12,801 --> 00:12:14,250
and why he was there.

186
00:12:14,354 --> 00:12:16,943
Get a shot in here.

187
00:12:17,046 --> 00:12:19,117
I want the same from the
first firemen on the scene.

188
00:12:19,221 --> 00:12:21,326
I want to see it exactly
the way they saw it.

189
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:23,535
Joe.

190
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:25,952
Looks like she was a nurse.

191
00:12:26,055 --> 00:12:29,058
Charlie, get over to
Lakeshore Medical Center.

192
00:12:29,162 --> 00:12:30,922
Secure the possessions
of Terry Deveroux.

193
00:12:31,026 --> 00:12:32,441
Take care of it yourself.
It's critical.

194
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:33,442
No mistakes.

195
00:12:33,545 --> 00:12:35,271
You got it.

196
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:36,686
Joe, look at her neck.

197
00:12:42,244 --> 00:12:43,763
Strangled.

198
00:12:43,866 --> 00:12:45,454
I guess.

199
00:12:45,557 --> 00:12:50,873
Then stabbed, then burned, on
top of what looks like rape.

200
00:12:50,977 --> 00:12:51,978
Unbelievable.

201
00:12:52,081 --> 00:12:52,944
JOE: What a waste.

202
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,224
Corner's in the hall, Joe.

203
00:12:57,328 --> 00:12:58,881
You want him to come
in and take the body?

204
00:12:58,985 --> 00:12:59,848
Send him in.

205
00:13:07,096 --> 00:13:09,685
"Get tickets for A.S."

206
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:11,687
See if you come up with a little
black booklet for any names

207
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,275
with the initials A.S.

208
00:13:13,378 --> 00:13:14,276
Maybe there's a Rolodex.

209
00:13:19,108 --> 00:13:22,802
Gentlemen, it's time to put
this unfortunate lady to rest.

210
00:13:35,331 --> 00:13:36,781
Honey, you are
so spacey tonight.

211
00:13:45,652 --> 00:13:47,516
[gasps]

212
00:13:47,619 --> 00:13:49,242
Renee?

213
00:13:49,345 --> 00:13:50,519
Are you OK?

214
00:13:50,622 --> 00:13:51,761
Oh!

215
00:13:51,865 --> 00:13:54,764
I had the most awful
images in my mind.

216
00:13:54,868 --> 00:13:55,973
Of what?

217
00:13:56,076 --> 00:13:59,459
Of, uh, men's faces, darkness.

218
00:14:02,186 --> 00:14:04,636
Were they people we know?

219
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:06,362
No.

220
00:14:06,466 --> 00:14:07,536
What were they doing?

221
00:14:07,639 --> 00:14:08,675
I don't know.

222
00:14:08,778 --> 00:14:13,473
They were just, um,
making everything dark.

223
00:14:13,576 --> 00:14:15,371
It was really scary.

224
00:14:15,475 --> 00:14:18,305
Honey, honey, it's your body
telling your mind time out.

225
00:14:18,409 --> 00:14:19,755
Stress.

226
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:24,139
You got a demanding job,
a miscarriage, money.

227
00:14:24,242 --> 00:14:25,416
You think?

228
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:28,971
Yeah, I think so.

229
00:14:29,075 --> 00:14:30,731
Oh.

230
00:14:30,835 --> 00:14:34,287
[music playing]

231
00:14:38,808 --> 00:14:39,706
Good morning.

232
00:14:45,677 --> 00:14:47,852
Are you OK?

233
00:14:47,956 --> 00:14:52,063
Um, why don't-- why don't
we go outside for a minute?

234
00:14:52,167 --> 00:14:53,030
OK.

235
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:58,173
Didn't you hear?

236
00:14:58,276 --> 00:14:59,622
No, what happened?

237
00:14:59,726 --> 00:15:01,314
Terry Deveroux was murdered.

238
00:15:07,665 --> 00:15:10,357
Oh, my god.

239
00:15:10,461 --> 00:15:11,703
Hey, Renee.

240
00:15:11,807 --> 00:15:13,119
Mrs. What's-her-name would
like to know if she's going

241
00:15:13,222 --> 00:15:14,706
to have her therapy now.

242
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:16,294
Can't you see that
I need some time?

243
00:15:19,366 --> 00:15:20,643
What's her problem?

244
00:15:20,747 --> 00:15:22,991
I just told her about Terry.

245
00:15:23,094 --> 00:15:24,440
Oh.

246
00:15:24,544 --> 00:15:25,925
They were friends, or--

247
00:15:26,028 --> 00:15:28,928
No, not really, but I
think everybody's upset.

248
00:15:29,031 --> 00:15:30,343
Yeah.

249
00:15:30,446 --> 00:15:32,310
WOMAN: Did you hear
what happened to Terry?

250
00:15:32,414 --> 00:15:35,382
I heard about it on
the radio coming in.

251
00:15:35,486 --> 00:15:37,591
The apartment was on fire.

252
00:15:37,695 --> 00:15:39,559
She was stabbed.

253
00:15:39,662 --> 00:15:43,045
WOMAN: Somebody told me the
police are coming here today.

254
00:15:43,149 --> 00:15:44,012
Help me, Renee.

255
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,363
You're gonna sit, Renee?

256
00:15:54,056 --> 00:15:54,954
Renee?

257
00:16:14,318 --> 00:16:15,526
Why don't you come
outside with us?

258
00:16:23,741 --> 00:16:25,363
Can I get you some water?

259
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:26,364
I'm all right.

260
00:16:33,268 --> 00:16:34,303
God, who could have done this?

261
00:16:37,203 --> 00:16:38,583
You've got to find out
who did this to her,

262
00:16:38,687 --> 00:16:40,137
and you make sure he pays.

263
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,586
That's my intention.

264
00:16:41,690 --> 00:16:42,484
I won't forget Terry.

265
00:16:42,587 --> 00:16:45,349
I promise you that.

266
00:16:45,452 --> 00:16:50,354
She had the sweetest,
most wonderful voice.

267
00:16:50,457 --> 00:16:51,700
I got a tape of her
outside in the car.

268
00:16:51,803 --> 00:16:52,942
I'd like you to hear it.

269
00:16:53,046 --> 00:16:55,083
A note was found in
Terry's apartment--

270
00:16:55,186 --> 00:16:57,464
"Get tickets for A.S."

271
00:16:57,568 --> 00:17:00,502
Do those initials
mean anything to you?

272
00:17:00,605 --> 00:17:02,538
Yes.

273
00:17:02,642 --> 00:17:05,990
Aerosmith, the band, they're
giving a concert next week.

274
00:17:06,094 --> 00:17:06,956
Check the ticket office.

275
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:09,890
Maybe she paid with
her credit card.

276
00:17:09,994 --> 00:17:12,686
Was Terry having a
problem with someone?

277
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:15,241
Any enemies that you knew of?

278
00:17:15,344 --> 00:17:16,173
Enemies?

279
00:17:16,276 --> 00:17:17,139
No.

280
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:22,662
Everybody who knew
her loved her.

281
00:17:22,765 --> 00:17:24,698
She was so special.

282
00:17:24,802 --> 00:17:27,839
The evidence indicates
that she let the attacker in.

283
00:17:27,943 --> 00:17:29,703
She knew him.

284
00:17:29,807 --> 00:17:30,911
There must have been somebody.

285
00:17:31,015 --> 00:17:34,570
OK, she did have
boyfriend problems.

286
00:17:34,674 --> 00:17:37,056
It's because they all want to
marry her after the first date.

287
00:17:37,159 --> 00:17:38,022
Can you give us some names?

288
00:17:38,126 --> 00:17:39,748
Sure.

289
00:17:39,851 --> 00:17:41,991
Eric Sylvester.

290
00:17:42,095 --> 00:17:44,684
He works at the hospital.

291
00:17:44,787 --> 00:17:46,513
You've got to stop making
those heartfelt promises

292
00:17:46,617 --> 00:17:47,790
to victims' families.

293
00:17:47,894 --> 00:17:49,033
No, I don't.

294
00:17:49,137 --> 00:17:50,483
That guy was grieving hard.

295
00:17:50,586 --> 00:17:51,967
He needed to hear we
were going to help him.

296
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,520
You just about guaranteed
him we'd break the case.

297
00:17:53,624 --> 00:17:54,418
What are we, roofers?

298
00:17:54,521 --> 00:17:55,833
You can't warranty police work.

299
00:17:55,936 --> 00:17:57,662
Maybe I should think
about a career change.

300
00:17:57,766 --> 00:17:59,043
Hello?

301
00:17:59,147 --> 00:18:00,596
Hello?
Hold on.

302
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,528
You're breaking up.

303
00:18:01,632 --> 00:18:02,460
Can you hear me?

304
00:18:02,564 --> 00:18:05,429
There-- there you go.

305
00:18:05,532 --> 00:18:07,845
All right, thanks.

306
00:18:07,948 --> 00:18:09,053
Well?

307
00:18:09,157 --> 00:18:11,538
Forensics couldn't
get any fingerprints.

308
00:18:11,642 --> 00:18:12,746
Off anything?

309
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:16,440
Water and smoke damage
wiped everything clean.

310
00:18:16,543 --> 00:18:17,820
Told you you
shouldn't make promises.

311
00:18:21,617 --> 00:18:24,586
I investigate 35
to 40 murders a year.

312
00:18:24,689 --> 00:18:26,726
But I think I reacted
to Terry Deveroux

313
00:18:26,829 --> 00:18:29,177
more as a parent than as a cop.

314
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:31,075
I couldn't help thinking
it just as easily could

315
00:18:31,179 --> 00:18:32,594
have been my daughter
who was murdered

316
00:18:32,697 --> 00:18:35,528
or who could have been next.

317
00:18:35,631 --> 00:18:40,671
Not finding Terry's killer
was never an option for me.

318
00:18:40,774 --> 00:18:43,363
If I can have everybody's
attention for a minute.

319
00:18:43,467 --> 00:18:45,020
I'm Joe Stachula.

320
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,090
This is Larry Ephron.

321
00:18:46,194 --> 00:18:47,747
We're the homicide
detectives investigating

322
00:18:47,850 --> 00:18:49,749
the murder of Terry Deveroux.

323
00:18:49,852 --> 00:18:52,407
We know you have
important work to do here,

324
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:55,064
but the only way we can
hope to solve this case

325
00:18:55,168 --> 00:18:57,722
is from some clue
you might have.

326
00:18:57,826 --> 00:19:00,622
We'll be asking some of you
to be available for questioning

327
00:19:00,725 --> 00:19:01,761
over the next several days.

328
00:19:01,864 --> 00:19:03,866
But if anyone
thinks of something

329
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:07,318
that might be able to help
us out, please let us know.

330
00:19:07,422 --> 00:19:08,492
Do you have any suspects?

331
00:19:08,595 --> 00:19:10,287
JOE: Right now, we
do have some leads,

332
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:12,668
but obviously we
can't disclose them.

333
00:19:12,772 --> 00:19:15,533
All I can say is
whoever committed

334
00:19:15,637 --> 00:19:19,882
this crime is an extremely
dangerous individual.

335
00:19:23,334 --> 00:19:25,992
So you dated on and off
for about six weeks,

336
00:19:26,095 --> 00:19:27,235
and then the relationship ended?

337
00:19:27,338 --> 00:19:28,753
How long ago?

338
00:19:28,857 --> 00:19:30,030
Three weeks.

339
00:19:30,134 --> 00:19:32,274
And was the breakup mutual?

340
00:19:32,378 --> 00:19:33,172
Not really.

341
00:19:33,275 --> 00:19:35,346
[SCOFFING] Not really.

342
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:37,555
You know, I keep
telling the wife, please

343
00:19:37,659 --> 00:19:38,763
don't answer me "not really."

344
00:19:38,867 --> 00:19:39,902
I don't get this expression.

345
00:19:40,006 --> 00:19:42,181
Is it yes but with a hint of no?

346
00:19:42,284 --> 00:19:43,561
No with a smidgen of yes?

347
00:19:43,665 --> 00:19:45,287
She broke up with me.

348
00:19:45,391 --> 00:19:47,600
Ah.

349
00:19:47,703 --> 00:19:49,533
I need to know where you
were the night of the 23rd.

350
00:19:54,641 --> 00:19:57,472
I went to dinner at
my brother's house.

351
00:19:57,575 --> 00:19:59,784
I was there all night.

352
00:19:59,888 --> 00:20:03,340
Look, Detective, I could
never hurt anyone like that,

353
00:20:03,443 --> 00:20:05,618
especially not Terry.

354
00:20:05,721 --> 00:20:07,344
I understand.

355
00:20:07,447 --> 00:20:08,310
OK.

356
00:20:11,140 --> 00:20:12,659
Can I get the number
of your brother?

357
00:20:12,763 --> 00:20:13,660
Sure.

358
00:20:13,764 --> 00:20:14,661
Hold on a second.

359
00:20:18,527 --> 00:20:19,321
Look.

360
00:20:19,425 --> 00:20:21,185
I don't believe it.

361
00:20:21,289 --> 00:20:22,186
That's a cop.

362
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,981
Looks like he was
questioning Eric.

363
00:20:24,084 --> 00:20:25,672
Eric?

364
00:20:25,776 --> 00:20:26,604
No way.

365
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:29,504
That dog don't hunt.

366
00:20:29,607 --> 00:20:30,953
Why did you say that?

367
00:20:31,057 --> 00:20:32,023
[screams]

368
00:20:32,127 --> 00:20:33,024
Renee?

369
00:20:35,717 --> 00:20:36,787
Uh, what?

370
00:20:36,890 --> 00:20:40,687
What you just said,
"that dog don't hunt."

371
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:42,482
Terry always used
that expression.

372
00:20:42,586 --> 00:20:44,346
She did?

373
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:46,314
For a minute, you
sounded just like her.

374
00:20:49,972 --> 00:20:52,596
Renee, pediatric
recovery's looking for you.

375
00:20:52,699 --> 00:20:54,011
OK.

376
00:20:54,114 --> 00:20:55,806
Hey, am I right, you haven't
treated anybody on this floor

377
00:20:55,909 --> 00:20:56,738
yet?

378
00:20:56,841 --> 00:20:58,049
Look, Nate, I'm sorry.

379
00:20:58,153 --> 00:20:59,913
I-- I don't feel very well.

380
00:21:00,017 --> 00:21:01,915
We're all upset about Terry.

381
00:21:02,019 --> 00:21:03,123
Yeah, that was
terrible, but we

382
00:21:03,227 --> 00:21:05,436
can't let it affect our work.

383
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:06,782
We all have jobs to do.

384
00:21:10,648 --> 00:21:13,617
Look, Nate, um, I'm going to
call downstairs for coverage.

385
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,584
I-- I should go home.

386
00:21:15,688 --> 00:21:18,000
No, Renee, that's really
not an option at this point.

387
00:21:18,104 --> 00:21:19,450
My patients are waiting
for their therapy.

388
00:21:19,554 --> 00:21:20,348
But, Nate--

389
00:21:20,451 --> 00:21:22,073
Look, I will call respiratory.

390
00:21:22,177 --> 00:21:23,730
I'll try to find
you some coverage.

391
00:21:23,834 --> 00:21:27,527
In the meantime, could you
just please get started?

392
00:21:27,631 --> 00:21:28,528
Fine.

393
00:21:32,463 --> 00:21:33,430
That's good, Mrs. Beevy.

394
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:34,396
That's fine.

395
00:21:38,089 --> 00:21:39,298
Good.

396
00:21:39,401 --> 00:21:40,160
Hey, Renee?

397
00:21:40,264 --> 00:21:41,403
Don't touch me!

398
00:21:41,507 --> 00:21:42,715
Sorry.

399
00:21:42,818 --> 00:21:43,957
No, sorry.

400
00:21:44,061 --> 00:21:45,787
I just wanted to say sorry
about before in there.

401
00:21:48,583 --> 00:21:49,687
What is the problem?

402
00:21:49,791 --> 00:21:50,654
You're the problem.

403
00:22:04,875 --> 00:22:05,669
I don't get it, Renee.

404
00:22:05,772 --> 00:22:06,601
The guy's not now.

405
00:22:06,704 --> 00:22:08,016
You've worked with
him for a while.

406
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:08,913
What's the problem?

407
00:22:09,017 --> 00:22:10,777
I don't know, Bill.

408
00:22:10,881 --> 00:22:13,642
He just makes my flesh crawl.

409
00:22:13,746 --> 00:22:17,197
I keep seeing these
things in my mind.

410
00:22:17,301 --> 00:22:18,509
Like last night?

411
00:22:18,613 --> 00:22:21,581
Yeah, but worse.

412
00:22:21,685 --> 00:22:23,203
I keep seeing these
hideous images

413
00:22:23,307 --> 00:22:25,171
of Terry Deveroux's murder.

414
00:22:25,274 --> 00:22:26,379
OK, that was--

415
00:22:26,483 --> 00:22:27,829
that was horrible.

416
00:22:27,932 --> 00:22:29,934
Everybody's shaken up about it.

417
00:22:30,038 --> 00:22:32,247
It's normal to imagine
the details you've heard.

418
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:34,249
Well, what if I haven't
heard any of these details

419
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:35,630
I'm seeing?

420
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:38,253
Then, it's your imagination,
working on the story you heard.

421
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:44,915
I even thought I saw
Terry today, in the lounge.

422
00:22:45,018 --> 00:22:50,334
Honey, it's a big deal.

423
00:22:50,438 --> 00:22:52,854
Your coworker was murdered.

424
00:22:52,957 --> 00:22:55,201
Trust me, you're
not going crazy.

425
00:23:24,437 --> 00:23:27,889
TERRY: [screaming]

426
00:23:52,603 --> 00:23:53,466
Uh.

427
00:24:02,199 --> 00:24:05,167
RENEE: [gasps]

428
00:24:05,271 --> 00:24:06,237
Honey?

429
00:24:06,341 --> 00:24:07,238
Are you still up?

430
00:24:14,073 --> 00:24:14,970
What is it?

431
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,354
Renee?

432
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:23,427
[gasping and screaming]

433
00:24:26,395 --> 00:24:27,776
What-- what's wrong?

434
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,743
What's wrong?

435
00:24:28,846 --> 00:24:29,675
Shh.

436
00:24:29,778 --> 00:24:32,712
What's wrong, honey?

437
00:24:32,816 --> 00:24:34,714
Shh.

438
00:24:34,818 --> 00:24:37,683
[wind blowing]

439
00:24:37,786 --> 00:24:41,238
[screams]

440
00:24:55,632 --> 00:24:57,081
Renee?

441
00:24:57,185 --> 00:24:59,498
I'm not Renee.

442
00:24:59,601 --> 00:25:00,464
Stop it, Renee.

443
00:25:04,088 --> 00:25:05,158
I'm Terry Deveroux.

444
00:25:07,747 --> 00:25:10,439
He killed me.

445
00:25:10,543 --> 00:25:12,338
The police don't know who he is.

446
00:25:12,441 --> 00:25:13,512
You have to tell them.

447
00:25:35,982 --> 00:25:39,917
[dog barking]

448
00:25:49,651 --> 00:25:50,997
REPORTER [ON RADIO]:
Good morning, Chicago.

449
00:25:51,101 --> 00:25:52,654
The traffic and weather
report is brought--

450
00:25:55,174 --> 00:25:56,071
Oh, god.

451
00:25:59,523 --> 00:26:02,526
How are you?

452
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:04,528
Not good.

453
00:26:04,632 --> 00:26:07,151
I feel hung over or something.

454
00:26:10,361 --> 00:26:13,226
You fell asleep in your clothes.

455
00:26:13,330 --> 00:26:17,092
Honey, I don't want
you to get scared,

456
00:26:17,196 --> 00:26:21,545
but, uh, something
happened last night.

457
00:26:21,649 --> 00:26:25,860
You had some kind of
cataleptic seizure.

458
00:26:25,963 --> 00:26:26,861
What?

459
00:26:26,964 --> 00:26:29,001
At least I think
that's what it was.

460
00:26:29,104 --> 00:26:31,072
And then when I went
to touch you, you--

461
00:26:31,175 --> 00:26:32,591
you went all rigid.

462
00:26:32,694 --> 00:26:34,247
And you seemed like you
were going to be all right,

463
00:26:34,351 --> 00:26:36,974
and then you started screaming.

464
00:26:39,770 --> 00:26:43,636
Whatever it is, we'll
take care of it.

465
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:45,362
I want you to get a
complete physical.

466
00:26:45,465 --> 00:26:46,674
What do you think's
wrong with me?

467
00:26:46,777 --> 00:26:49,953
I-- I'm not sure.

468
00:26:50,056 --> 00:26:55,061
You told me you
were Terry Deveroux.

469
00:26:58,099 --> 00:26:59,376
Oh, my god.

470
00:27:12,423 --> 00:27:13,701
I won't take long, Terry.

471
00:27:20,121 --> 00:27:21,605
Just take five minutes.

472
00:27:21,709 --> 00:27:25,436
[gasps] Oh, my
god, it was you!

473
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:26,437
Excuse me?

474
00:27:38,864 --> 00:27:41,073
Hey, I want to talk to you.

475
00:27:43,834 --> 00:27:44,801
WOMAN: Hi, Adam.
- Hi.

476
00:27:44,904 --> 00:27:45,767
How you doing?

477
00:27:52,049 --> 00:27:52,981
Please, wait!

478
00:27:53,085 --> 00:27:54,465
Leave me alone!

479
00:27:58,193 --> 00:27:59,470
Renee!

480
00:27:59,574 --> 00:28:01,541
Just tell me why you said that!

481
00:28:08,272 --> 00:28:10,896
Hey, Renee, what's--
calm down, calm down.

482
00:28:10,999 --> 00:28:12,967
What's wrong?

483
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:13,864
I can't, um--

484
00:28:13,968 --> 00:28:14,762
What is it?

485
00:28:14,865 --> 00:28:15,659
Come here.

486
00:28:15,763 --> 00:28:16,660
Come on, come on.

487
00:28:16,764 --> 00:28:17,661
My goodness.

488
00:28:23,253 --> 00:28:25,048
What happened to you?

489
00:28:25,151 --> 00:28:27,188
You're never going
to believe this.

490
00:28:27,291 --> 00:28:29,466
Adam Schuster just
followed me off an elevator

491
00:28:29,569 --> 00:28:30,881
and chased me up the stairs.
- What?

492
00:28:30,985 --> 00:28:31,779
Why?

493
00:28:31,882 --> 00:28:33,781
He's a maniac.

494
00:28:33,884 --> 00:28:34,713
Hi, Adam.

495
00:28:34,816 --> 00:28:35,714
Hi.

496
00:28:38,820 --> 00:28:39,614
Morning, Clara.

497
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:41,202
Good morning.

498
00:28:41,305 --> 00:28:46,069
I, uh, I think he's
the one who killed Terry.

499
00:28:46,172 --> 00:28:47,311
Why on earth?

500
00:28:50,314 --> 00:28:52,213
Where did you get that from?

501
00:28:52,316 --> 00:28:53,110
Nowhere.

502
00:28:53,214 --> 00:28:54,525
I, uh--

503
00:28:54,629 --> 00:28:59,876
JENNY: Renee, tell me.

504
00:28:59,979 --> 00:29:00,946
Come here.

505
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,023
What did you hear?

506
00:29:12,923 --> 00:29:16,685
OK, uh, this is
going to sound crazy.

507
00:29:19,378 --> 00:29:23,140
I keep seeing the murder
in my mind, visions of it.

508
00:29:23,244 --> 00:29:24,659
Adam is there, and he's--

509
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:29,802
it's horrible what
he's doing to her.

510
00:29:29,906 --> 00:29:31,873
Look, I'm sorry, but
I'm not getting this.

511
00:29:31,977 --> 00:29:34,669
Do you think you're
psychic or something?

512
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:35,877
I don't know.

513
00:29:35,981 --> 00:29:37,603
I can't explain it.

514
00:29:37,706 --> 00:29:40,813
But, Renee, you were barely
friends with Terry, right?

515
00:29:40,917 --> 00:29:42,642
So why would this
be happening to you?

516
00:29:42,746 --> 00:29:44,575
Jenny, I wish I knew.

517
00:29:44,679 --> 00:29:46,508
JENNY: Of all people,
Adam Schuster?

518
00:29:46,612 --> 00:29:48,683
I can't believe
he'd be a murderer.

519
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:51,306
He's just such an ordinary guy.

520
00:29:51,410 --> 00:29:52,307
No, he's not.

521
00:30:02,766 --> 00:30:04,147
Retractor, please.

522
00:30:04,250 --> 00:30:05,217
I'll need wet laps.

523
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:08,392
And have your suction ready.

524
00:30:08,496 --> 00:30:09,393
Easy does it.

525
00:30:09,497 --> 00:30:10,463
[device beeping]

526
00:30:10,567 --> 00:30:11,879
Doctor, her blood
pressure's dropping.

527
00:30:11,982 --> 00:30:13,225
How fast?

528
00:30:13,328 --> 00:30:14,640
80 over 60.

529
00:30:14,743 --> 00:30:16,435
I'm having some
problems ventilating her.

530
00:30:16,538 --> 00:30:19,196
[device beeping]

531
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:20,888
There's not much bleeding.

532
00:30:20,991 --> 00:30:22,682
78 over 54.

533
00:30:22,786 --> 00:30:25,168
I'm cutting back
on the anesthesia.

534
00:30:25,271 --> 00:30:26,755
68 over 40.

535
00:30:26,859 --> 00:30:27,998
Still ventilating poorly.

536
00:30:28,102 --> 00:30:32,520
Dr. Carter, the, uh,
diaphragm is pushing down.

537
00:30:32,623 --> 00:30:35,143
Could this be a
tension pneumothorax?

538
00:30:35,247 --> 00:30:36,110
He's right.

539
00:30:36,213 --> 00:30:37,870
Get him a number
16 angiocath set.

540
00:30:37,974 --> 00:30:39,907
[device beeping]

541
00:30:42,910 --> 00:30:43,807
Good work.

542
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:50,641
Hey, Doc.

543
00:30:50,745 --> 00:30:52,402
What's up, Joe?

544
00:30:52,505 --> 00:30:53,679
I was just in
the neighborhood.

545
00:30:53,782 --> 00:30:55,267
Thought I'd stop by to see
if you had the Deveroux--

546
00:30:55,370 --> 00:30:56,164
Deveroux results.

547
00:30:56,268 --> 00:30:58,615
On the table behind you.

548
00:30:58,718 --> 00:31:00,306
I'm not entirely
sure the ink is dry.

549
00:31:00,410 --> 00:31:01,204
Huh?

550
00:31:01,307 --> 00:31:02,377
What?

551
00:31:02,481 --> 00:31:03,447
Oh.

552
00:31:03,551 --> 00:31:04,345
It is.

553
00:31:04,448 --> 00:31:05,242
How's it going?

554
00:31:05,346 --> 00:31:06,381
Ah, it's going.

555
00:31:06,485 --> 00:31:07,762
Could be better.

556
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:10,213
We had one suspect, but it
was the victim's ex-boyfriend.

557
00:31:10,316 --> 00:31:12,663
His alibi stuck.

558
00:31:12,767 --> 00:31:14,838
I was hoping maybe
you had something.

559
00:31:14,942 --> 00:31:16,978
A little surprise, maybe.

560
00:31:17,082 --> 00:31:20,257
She wasn't raped.

561
00:31:20,361 --> 00:31:22,225
Well, we'll keep that
under our hats, won't we?

562
00:31:22,328 --> 00:31:24,261
Anybody else know
that, he's our man.

563
00:31:24,365 --> 00:31:25,366
I'd say so.

564
00:31:25,469 --> 00:31:26,367
Thanks, Doc.

565
00:31:35,583 --> 00:31:37,723
Oh!

566
00:31:37,826 --> 00:31:40,174
Hi, honey.

567
00:31:40,277 --> 00:31:41,485
What's up?

568
00:31:41,589 --> 00:31:42,659
I don't know.

569
00:31:42,762 --> 00:31:44,903
I love my job, and I love you.

570
00:31:45,006 --> 00:31:45,834
- Oh.
- You know what else?

571
00:31:45,938 --> 00:31:47,043
What?

572
00:31:47,146 --> 00:31:48,458
We're going out to dinner
tonight, someplace nice.

573
00:31:48,561 --> 00:31:49,355
Mm.

574
00:31:49,459 --> 00:31:50,425
Mhm.

575
00:31:50,529 --> 00:31:51,702
We deserve it or what?

576
00:31:51,806 --> 00:31:52,600
Don't answer that.

577
00:31:52,703 --> 00:31:55,051
Just be there.

578
00:31:55,154 --> 00:31:56,362
[giggles]

579
00:32:04,370 --> 00:32:05,164
Come in.

580
00:32:05,268 --> 00:32:06,096
Hey.

581
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,063
Hi, Renee!

582
00:32:07,166 --> 00:32:08,788
Nate Bradshaw spoke to me today.

583
00:32:08,892 --> 00:32:09,893
Oh.

584
00:32:09,997 --> 00:32:11,101
Talk about jumping the gun.

585
00:32:11,205 --> 00:32:12,896
I was just a little
tardy, making my rounds.

586
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,554
No, Renee, this is
about Adam Schuster.

587
00:32:15,657 --> 00:32:17,659
It seems Adam is very upset.

588
00:32:17,763 --> 00:32:19,075
Nate actually had
to talk him out

589
00:32:19,178 --> 00:32:21,146
of filing a formal grievance.

590
00:32:21,249 --> 00:32:23,562
He thought best to speak
to me unofficially first

591
00:32:23,665 --> 00:32:25,081
and maybe we could clear it up.

592
00:32:25,184 --> 00:32:26,703
Adam says you refuse
to work with him.

593
00:32:26,806 --> 00:32:27,600
Is that true?

594
00:32:27,704 --> 00:32:28,981
No.

595
00:32:29,085 --> 00:32:30,810
He says you went so far as
to tell one of the other nurses

596
00:32:30,914 --> 00:32:34,435
that he killed poor
Terry Deveroux.

597
00:32:34,538 --> 00:32:37,817
Is he now spying on me?

598
00:32:37,921 --> 00:32:42,512
OK, look, uh, Donna, the
truth is I don't like him.

599
00:32:42,615 --> 00:32:43,409
He's strange.

600
00:32:43,513 --> 00:32:44,583
He followed me.

601
00:32:44,686 --> 00:32:45,929
He literally chased me
up a flight of stairs.

602
00:32:46,033 --> 00:32:47,172
He did?

603
00:32:47,275 --> 00:32:49,381
Did he threaten you, or
was there physical contact?

604
00:32:49,484 --> 00:32:50,899
No, he never caught up to me.

605
00:32:51,003 --> 00:32:53,109
How long have you been
having problems with him?

606
00:32:53,212 --> 00:32:54,006
[siren blaring]

607
00:32:54,110 --> 00:32:54,973
Adam?

608
00:32:57,527 --> 00:33:00,219
I guess ever since Terry
Deveroux was murdered.

609
00:33:00,323 --> 00:33:02,842
Nate really likes
this guy, Renee.

610
00:33:02,946 --> 00:33:06,156
Do yourself a favor, try to find
a way to get along with him.

611
00:33:09,608 --> 00:33:10,402
BILL: Honey?

612
00:33:10,505 --> 00:33:12,852
I'm home.

613
00:33:12,956 --> 00:33:14,578
Guess where I made reservations?

614
00:33:14,682 --> 00:33:16,442
I'll give you a hint.

615
00:33:16,546 --> 00:33:20,032
You want to wear that cool
dress, the one with the straps?

616
00:33:23,208 --> 00:33:24,174
What's wrong?

617
00:33:24,278 --> 00:33:25,417
Hideous headache.

618
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,970
Aw.

619
00:33:27,074 --> 00:33:28,730
What happened?

620
00:33:28,834 --> 00:33:30,042
Schuster again?

621
00:33:30,146 --> 00:33:31,423
Yep.

622
00:33:31,526 --> 00:33:34,840
He got Nate to talk
to Donna about me.

623
00:33:34,943 --> 00:33:36,911
I really think they're
going to fire me.

624
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:39,051
Ah, to hell with
them If they do.

625
00:33:39,155 --> 00:33:41,433
Well, you're feeling awfully
confident about this job.

626
00:33:41,536 --> 00:33:44,056
Yes, in fact, I am.

627
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:46,369
Knock wood.

628
00:33:46,472 --> 00:33:47,508
Honey, I'm beat.

629
00:33:47,611 --> 00:33:50,752
I'm just going to go
upstairs and lay down.

630
00:33:50,856 --> 00:33:51,995
Sorry about tonight.

631
00:33:52,099 --> 00:33:53,065
Don't worry about it, honey.

632
00:34:08,943 --> 00:34:09,840
Renee?

633
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,223
Honey?

634
00:34:21,542 --> 00:34:23,406
Renee, look at me.

635
00:34:27,893 --> 00:34:30,344
[screams]

636
00:34:39,836 --> 00:34:42,356
Leave her alone.

637
00:34:42,459 --> 00:34:46,325
Please go away.

638
00:34:46,429 --> 00:34:48,293
Did you call the police?

639
00:34:48,396 --> 00:34:49,466
Renee.

640
00:34:49,570 --> 00:34:52,504
You know I'm not Renee.

641
00:34:52,607 --> 00:34:54,851
Why won't you help me?

642
00:34:54,954 --> 00:34:56,163
What do you want from us?

643
00:34:56,266 --> 00:35:01,996
You have your life,
but mine is gone.

644
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:03,170
Tell me what
you want me to do.

645
00:35:06,311 --> 00:35:09,141
Go to the police.

646
00:35:09,245 --> 00:35:12,351
Tell them Adam
Schuster killed me.

647
00:35:15,734 --> 00:35:17,322
Make them punish him.

648
00:35:30,266 --> 00:35:31,784
It happened again, didn't it?

649
00:35:35,512 --> 00:35:36,306
Oh, god, Bill.

650
00:35:36,410 --> 00:35:37,618
Am I going crazy?

651
00:35:40,793 --> 00:35:41,760
If you are, then I am.

652
00:35:45,281 --> 00:35:50,009
What did-- what did she say?

653
00:35:53,806 --> 00:35:55,532
She told me to tell
the police who her is.

654
00:35:55,636 --> 00:35:58,604
She-- she said he's--

655
00:35:58,708 --> 00:35:59,605
I know who he is.

656
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:03,057
Adam Schuster.

657
00:36:31,844 --> 00:36:37,402
Um, I-- I'm just going to talk.

658
00:36:37,505 --> 00:36:39,162
I got the feeling we would
have been good friends.

659
00:36:43,615 --> 00:36:49,414
I'm really sorry you died,
what happened to you.

660
00:36:54,971 --> 00:36:56,179
But we're not friends.

661
00:37:00,321 --> 00:37:04,256
I can't make them believe me.

662
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,706
You should find somebody else.

663
00:37:24,172 --> 00:37:25,346
Can I help you?

664
00:37:25,450 --> 00:37:27,314
Yeah, I'm just, uh,
looking for the workup

665
00:37:27,417 --> 00:37:30,213
on Renee Perkins.

666
00:37:30,317 --> 00:37:35,494
Um, you didn't order these
tests, did you, Doctor?

667
00:37:35,598 --> 00:37:36,426
No.

668
00:37:36,530 --> 00:37:39,153
I'm, uh, I'm her husband.

669
00:37:39,257 --> 00:37:40,672
Yeah, well, normally
these are only released

670
00:37:40,775 --> 00:37:41,914
to the attending physician.

671
00:37:42,018 --> 00:37:45,677
Well, I promise I
won't tell if you don't.

672
00:37:45,780 --> 00:37:46,850
I can keep a secret.

673
00:37:46,954 --> 00:37:47,851
Thank you.

674
00:37:53,892 --> 00:37:56,826
[phone ringing]

675
00:37:57,689 --> 00:37:58,931
Hello?
BILL [ON PHONE]: Hi.

676
00:37:59,035 --> 00:38:00,036
It's me.

677
00:38:00,139 --> 00:38:01,209
Great news.

678
00:38:01,313 --> 00:38:03,626
All your tests were normal.

679
00:38:03,729 --> 00:38:05,075
That's a relief.

680
00:38:05,179 --> 00:38:06,318
What's wrong?

681
00:38:06,422 --> 00:38:09,597
Well, if it's not a medical
issue, then what is it?

682
00:38:12,669 --> 00:38:13,532
I'm gonna call you later.

683
00:38:18,434 --> 00:38:22,196
Is your, um, friend a,
uh, member of the church?

684
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:26,338
Yes, she is, but she's
not active anymore.

685
00:38:26,442 --> 00:38:28,375
I think she regrets that
now, especially with all

686
00:38:28,478 --> 00:38:30,169
she's going through.

687
00:38:30,273 --> 00:38:31,964
I don't know much
about possessions

688
00:38:32,068 --> 00:38:33,449
beyond the church protocol.

689
00:38:33,552 --> 00:38:38,419
It requires a battery of
tests; medical, psychological.

690
00:38:38,523 --> 00:38:42,320
And, uh, then if the person
gets a clean bill of health,

691
00:38:42,423 --> 00:38:46,910
I believe a board meets to see
if an exorcism is necessary.

692
00:38:47,014 --> 00:38:48,395
An exorcism?

693
00:38:48,498 --> 00:38:49,913
Oh, yeah.

694
00:38:50,017 --> 00:38:51,294
Does it trouble you?

695
00:38:51,398 --> 00:38:55,712
Father, has anyone ever been
possessed by a good spirit?

696
00:38:55,816 --> 00:38:58,784
I mean, it isn't always a
demon or a devil, is it?

697
00:38:58,888 --> 00:39:01,269
Well, I, uh, never
thought about it.

698
00:39:01,373 --> 00:39:02,995
I suppose it's possible,
but then again,

699
00:39:03,099 --> 00:39:04,859
why isn't it at rest in heaven?

700
00:39:04,963 --> 00:39:06,516
Maybe it needs help.

701
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:11,245
Maybe if the person possessed
did with the spirit asked,

702
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:13,730
maybe it could rest.

703
00:39:13,834 --> 00:39:20,150
I'm afraid I'm outside of my
realm of experience on this.

704
00:39:20,254 --> 00:39:22,877
I've wasted
enough of your time.

705
00:39:22,981 --> 00:39:25,811
Thank you, Father.

706
00:39:25,915 --> 00:39:29,056
Is there something more
you'd like to talk about?

707
00:39:29,159 --> 00:39:31,023
No, I don't think so.

708
00:39:31,127 --> 00:39:34,164
I'll pray for you.

709
00:39:34,268 --> 00:39:35,165
Thank you.

710
00:39:37,685 --> 00:39:38,479
MAN: Here you go.

711
00:39:38,583 --> 00:39:39,687
Thank you.

712
00:39:39,791 --> 00:39:41,033
Pizza.

713
00:39:41,137 --> 00:39:42,552
Pizza, pizza.

714
00:39:42,656 --> 00:39:44,105
They told me you'd be
here feeding your face.

715
00:39:44,209 --> 00:39:45,555
Hey, Bill.
How's it going, man?

716
00:39:45,659 --> 00:39:47,557
How's the wild and crazy world
of the surgical resident?

717
00:39:47,661 --> 00:39:49,214
- I can smell the finish line.
- I hear you.

718
00:39:49,317 --> 00:39:50,215
You doing the interview thing?

719
00:39:50,318 --> 00:39:51,147
Oh, yeah.

720
00:39:51,250 --> 00:39:52,044
How about you?

721
00:39:52,148 --> 00:39:53,494
Nothing but.

722
00:39:53,598 --> 00:39:56,773
Capital District Psych Center,
Denver Psych, Boston General,

723
00:39:56,877 --> 00:39:58,706
all in one month.

724
00:39:58,810 --> 00:40:02,054
So, uh, I actually
wanted a consult.

725
00:40:02,158 --> 00:40:03,262
Delighted.

726
00:40:03,366 --> 00:40:04,643
It's a doozy.

727
00:40:04,747 --> 00:40:07,888
These, uh, people
I know, um, really

728
00:40:07,991 --> 00:40:11,650
steady, down-to-earth,
normal, having a rough time.

729
00:40:11,754 --> 00:40:14,929
The, uh-- the wife, uh--

730
00:40:15,033 --> 00:40:20,521
the wife believes she's been
possessed by the spirit of--

731
00:40:20,625 --> 00:40:23,835
by, by the spirit of the
nurse who was murdered.

732
00:40:23,938 --> 00:40:24,732
Oh, yeah?

733
00:40:24,836 --> 00:40:26,527
Wow.

734
00:40:26,631 --> 00:40:29,668
The husband has actually
witnessed these possessions.

735
00:40:29,772 --> 00:40:30,566
How many have there been?

736
00:40:30,669 --> 00:40:32,084
Two, and they're uncanny.

737
00:40:32,188 --> 00:40:35,916
Uh, some cataleptic symptoms--
stiff limbs, tremors.

738
00:40:36,019 --> 00:40:36,986
Her voice even changes.

739
00:40:37,089 --> 00:40:38,056
Oh, thanks.

740
00:40:38,159 --> 00:40:39,713
Uh, the dead woman
was from Louisiana,

741
00:40:39,816 --> 00:40:41,404
and during these
episodes, the wife--

742
00:40:41,508 --> 00:40:43,095
well, it just isn't her.

743
00:40:43,199 --> 00:40:45,650
It's someone else's
voice coming through.

744
00:40:45,753 --> 00:40:47,203
OK, this is great.

745
00:40:47,306 --> 00:40:49,792
I actually attended
a lecture on this.

746
00:40:49,895 --> 00:40:50,724
Possession?

747
00:40:50,827 --> 00:40:51,759
Of course not.

748
00:40:51,863 --> 00:40:54,106
Multiple personality disorder.

749
00:40:54,210 --> 00:40:55,625
Episodes of so-called
possession are

750
00:40:55,729 --> 00:40:57,316
commonplace in
third-world countries.

751
00:40:57,420 --> 00:40:59,595
Findings suggest
that possessions

752
00:40:59,698 --> 00:41:00,975
have much in common.

753
00:41:01,079 --> 00:41:02,149
Multiple personality disorder.

754
00:41:02,252 --> 00:41:04,323
It's not, uh--

755
00:41:04,427 --> 00:41:07,292
it's not multiple
personality disorder.

756
00:41:07,395 --> 00:41:09,605
You seem pretty sure of this.

757
00:41:09,708 --> 00:41:10,502
Wrong age.

758
00:41:10,606 --> 00:41:13,401
Wrong history.

759
00:41:13,505 --> 00:41:14,610
Wrong person.

760
00:41:14,713 --> 00:41:16,853
Does not fit the profile.

761
00:41:16,957 --> 00:41:20,823
Well, how else
do you explain it?

762
00:41:20,926 --> 00:41:24,723
Milosh, we're doctors.

763
00:41:24,827 --> 00:41:27,450
Don't we witness the
inexplicable time and again?

764
00:41:27,554 --> 00:41:29,107
Patients who should
die according

765
00:41:29,210 --> 00:41:31,281
to every scientific
fact available to us,

766
00:41:31,385 --> 00:41:32,420
and they don't.

767
00:41:32,524 --> 00:41:34,284
They heal by themselves.

768
00:41:34,388 --> 00:41:35,665
The patients we've
raised from the dead

769
00:41:35,769 --> 00:41:37,702
with electricity,
for Pete's sake.

770
00:41:37,805 --> 00:41:42,430
Isn't there room in
our universe for this?

771
00:41:42,534 --> 00:41:43,501
For possession?

772
00:41:57,894 --> 00:41:58,723
You're home early.

773
00:42:01,967 --> 00:42:02,830
Oh.

774
00:42:02,934 --> 00:42:03,831
Ooh.

775
00:42:09,803 --> 00:42:13,289
I absolutely don't want
you to see any shrinks.

776
00:42:13,392 --> 00:42:15,981
They'll wrap you up in
a tiny, little package

777
00:42:16,085 --> 00:42:18,121
and you'd never get out.

778
00:42:18,225 --> 00:42:20,330
So what are we going to do?

779
00:42:20,434 --> 00:42:21,608
Just pray it's finished.

780
00:42:21,711 --> 00:42:24,403
Bill, it's not
going to stop, not

781
00:42:24,507 --> 00:42:25,853
until we do what Terry asked.

782
00:42:25,957 --> 00:42:28,476
You go to the police and tell
them Adam Schuster killed her.

783
00:42:28,580 --> 00:42:30,030
Nuh-uh.
No.

784
00:42:30,133 --> 00:42:31,169
Never happened.

785
00:42:31,272 --> 00:42:32,998
No way.

786
00:42:33,102 --> 00:42:33,930
Why not?

787
00:42:34,034 --> 00:42:36,761
[scoffs] Are you kidding me?

788
00:42:36,864 --> 00:42:39,004
Just answer my question.

789
00:42:39,108 --> 00:42:41,766
If we both think it's true,
why can't we go to the police?

790
00:42:41,869 --> 00:42:44,527
Because the whole world will
say you're crazy, that's why.

791
00:42:44,631 --> 00:42:47,012
Well, I'm not
entirely sure I care.

792
00:42:47,116 --> 00:42:48,151
But you will.

793
00:42:48,255 --> 00:42:50,257
People will never look
at you the same way.

794
00:42:53,225 --> 00:42:56,539
Or is it they won't
look at you the same way?

795
00:42:56,643 --> 00:42:58,506
Poor Dr. Perkins,
married to a Loony Tune?

796
00:42:58,610 --> 00:42:59,404
You're not funny.

797
00:42:59,507 --> 00:43:01,199
I'm not trying to be.

798
00:43:01,302 --> 00:43:02,994
You're worried
about appearances.

799
00:43:03,097 --> 00:43:03,926
Of course I am!

800
00:43:04,029 --> 00:43:06,687
How else do people judge you?

801
00:43:06,791 --> 00:43:08,068
Bill, this is too important.

802
00:43:08,171 --> 00:43:10,035
No, I'll tell you
what's important,

803
00:43:10,139 --> 00:43:12,003
eight years of our lives.

804
00:43:12,106 --> 00:43:15,800
We've worked and struggled
and sacrificed, not

805
00:43:15,903 --> 00:43:17,215
to mention assumed heavy debts.

806
00:43:17,318 --> 00:43:18,181
Also, I can have this career.

807
00:43:18,285 --> 00:43:19,286
Yeah, I know all that.

808
00:43:19,389 --> 00:43:20,977
And now-- and now
when we're a heartbeat

809
00:43:21,081 --> 00:43:23,808
away from the payoff--

810
00:43:23,911 --> 00:43:24,740
no.

811
00:43:24,843 --> 00:43:26,155
I'm sorry.

812
00:43:26,258 --> 00:43:28,295
I'm not going to throw it all
away by making public jackasses

813
00:43:28,398 --> 00:43:31,091
