922
00:49:29,138 --> 00:49:29,932
MAN: Watch the door.

923
00:49:30,036 --> 00:49:32,866
MAN: Keep coming, now.

924
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:33,936
That's good, angle.

925
00:49:39,321 --> 00:49:40,218
Hey.

926
00:49:44,464 --> 00:49:45,361
How you doing?

927
00:49:48,123 --> 00:49:49,469
Better, when I'm done here.

928
00:49:54,370 --> 00:49:56,855
What do I do with this?

929
00:49:56,959 --> 00:49:57,891
How do you wrap up a life?

930
00:50:00,790 --> 00:50:02,827
You remember how they lived.

931
00:50:02,930 --> 00:50:03,862
You learn from it.

932
00:50:16,461 --> 00:50:17,359
Hey, Bill!

933
00:50:21,294 --> 00:50:22,088
Bill.

934
00:50:22,191 --> 00:50:23,468
Hey.

935
00:50:23,572 --> 00:50:26,644
I wanted to pick up on our
conversation the other day.

936
00:50:26,747 --> 00:50:29,647
That was Renee you were
talking about, wasn't it?

937
00:50:29,750 --> 00:50:30,544
[sighs]

938
00:50:30,648 --> 00:50:31,580
I apologize.

939
00:50:31,683 --> 00:50:33,685
It hit me later.

940
00:50:33,789 --> 00:50:35,618
My professional
enthusiasm overwhelmed

941
00:50:35,722 --> 00:50:37,137
what's left of my sensitivity.

942
00:50:37,241 --> 00:50:38,311
I'm sorry.

943
00:50:38,414 --> 00:50:39,933
What is going on?

944
00:50:40,037 --> 00:50:40,934
I already told you.

945
00:50:45,042 --> 00:50:48,321
It was like walking into
the Twilight Zone, man.

946
00:50:48,424 --> 00:50:49,908
Can you think of what
could be troubling her?

947
00:50:50,012 --> 00:50:50,806
Stress?

948
00:50:50,909 --> 00:50:51,945
Trauma?

949
00:50:52,049 --> 00:50:53,981
Well, we've both been
worried about money.

950
00:50:54,085 --> 00:50:56,881
In the last month, she--

951
00:50:56,984 --> 00:50:58,434
she had a miscarriage.

952
00:50:58,538 --> 00:51:00,195
Ah, well.

953
00:51:00,298 --> 00:51:03,819
If you'd seen what I saw,
you wouldn't be saying, ah.

954
00:51:03,922 --> 00:51:07,857
Anyway, I got a brand
new problem now.

955
00:51:07,961 --> 00:51:09,204
She wants to go to the police.

956
00:51:09,307 --> 00:51:12,069
Oh, no way.

957
00:51:12,172 --> 00:51:14,278
Well, you-- you're
not going to, are you?

958
00:51:14,381 --> 00:51:16,245
I don't want to.

959
00:51:16,349 --> 00:51:18,834
You don't sound
very convincing.

960
00:51:18,937 --> 00:51:19,869
Come on, buddy.

961
00:51:19,973 --> 00:51:20,905
You've got to ask
yourself, are you

962
00:51:21,008 --> 00:51:23,701
ready to sacrifice your career?

963
00:51:23,804 --> 00:51:25,116
We're talking about
my wife, Milosh.

964
00:51:25,220 --> 00:51:26,013
But--

965
00:51:26,117 --> 00:51:27,705
My-- no, no.

966
00:51:27,808 --> 00:51:29,120
It's my wife's peace of mind.

967
00:51:40,131 --> 00:51:42,099
Stachula, Evanston PD called.

968
00:51:42,202 --> 00:51:44,515
A couple out there want to
discuss the Deveroux case.

969
00:51:47,690 --> 00:51:49,313
JOE: I love when the
Dodgers come to Chicago.

970
00:51:49,416 --> 00:51:50,210
That's a rivalry.

971
00:51:50,314 --> 00:51:51,625
Well, I hope you
like it strong.

972
00:51:51,729 --> 00:51:52,833
Oh, not for me.

973
00:51:52,937 --> 00:51:53,869
Thank you.

974
00:51:53,972 --> 00:51:54,835
Thanks.

975
00:51:54,939 --> 00:51:58,874
Please, uh, have
a seat, Detective.

976
00:51:58,977 --> 00:52:00,703
Thanks for calling in.

977
00:52:00,807 --> 00:52:02,498
I appreciate anything
you have to tell me.

978
00:52:02,602 --> 00:52:05,605
Let me just start
by saying, uh, we

979
00:52:05,708 --> 00:52:08,228
don't want to have to
testify, I mean, go to court.

980
00:52:08,332 --> 00:52:09,988
Oh, we want our
names kept out of this.

981
00:52:10,092 --> 00:52:12,646
Yeah, I understand that.

982
00:52:12,750 --> 00:52:15,028
OK.

983
00:52:15,132 --> 00:52:20,067
Uh, Detective, have you
ever had any experience

984
00:52:20,171 --> 00:52:22,587
with the supernatural?

985
00:52:22,691 --> 00:52:24,141
No.

986
00:52:24,244 --> 00:52:27,454
Then this is going
to sound crazy to you.

987
00:52:27,558 --> 00:52:30,423
JOE: You know, police work,
you learn to keep an open mind,

988
00:52:30,526 --> 00:52:32,321
so go on.

989
00:52:35,738 --> 00:52:38,914
Um, well, we think
what we have is genuine

990
00:52:39,017 --> 00:52:42,020
information about your
case, but it's, um--

991
00:52:42,124 --> 00:52:44,091
it's come to me through--

992
00:52:44,195 --> 00:52:48,958
I guess I would call them, uh,
visions, and then two episodes

993
00:52:49,062 --> 00:52:52,962
of spirit possessions.

994
00:52:53,066 --> 00:52:56,173
Mr. Stachula, We aren't kooks.

995
00:52:56,276 --> 00:52:58,209
Bill is a surgeon, and I'm
a respiratory therapist

996
00:52:58,313 --> 00:52:59,935
at Lake Shore.

997
00:53:00,038 --> 00:53:02,593
We did not ask for
this to happen to us.

998
00:53:02,696 --> 00:53:05,941
BILL: I believe Renee was
possessed by the spirit

999
00:53:06,044 --> 00:53:08,046
of Terry Deveroux.

1000
00:53:08,150 --> 00:53:09,427
She identified herself.

1001
00:53:09,531 --> 00:53:15,571
She, uh-- Renee spoke with an
accent, uh, Southern, Cajun.

1002
00:53:15,675 --> 00:53:17,159
You heard her say this?

1003
00:53:17,263 --> 00:53:19,679
You didn't-- you
didn't see anything?

1004
00:53:19,782 --> 00:53:20,818
You heard this?

1005
00:53:20,921 --> 00:53:22,958
Yeah, absolutely.

1006
00:53:23,061 --> 00:53:26,410
Uh, she said that the police
weren't on the right track.

1007
00:53:26,513 --> 00:53:31,242
She said that the killer
is a nursing assistant

1008
00:53:31,346 --> 00:53:34,349
at Lake Shore, Adam Schuster.

1009
00:53:34,452 --> 00:53:35,315
Adam Schuster?

1010
00:53:41,770 --> 00:53:44,117
This just doesn't feel right.

1011
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:48,225
Uh, Renee, maybe we should just
apologize and back off here.

1012
00:53:48,328 --> 00:53:51,435
Dr. Perkins, I find
this very interesting.

1013
00:53:51,538 --> 00:53:54,852
I don't mind telling you that
this has been a tough case,

1014
00:53:54,955 --> 00:53:59,201
so please go on.

1015
00:53:59,305 --> 00:54:00,823
Well, uh, there
isn't much more.

1016
00:54:00,927 --> 00:54:03,826
It's just, um, there's
something I read

1017
00:54:03,930 --> 00:54:07,140
in the papers that isn't right.

1018
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:09,487
He didn't rape her.

1019
00:54:09,591 --> 00:54:11,627
He just arranged her
body to look like rape.

1020
00:54:17,323 --> 00:54:18,669
Joe, listen to me.

1021
00:54:22,845 --> 00:54:25,503
Do not type this report up, Joe.

1022
00:54:25,607 --> 00:54:28,265
We do not have to go on record
with every fruitcake who

1023
00:54:28,368 --> 00:54:31,544
calls in to report the martians
are landing on Lakeshore Drive.

1024
00:54:31,647 --> 00:54:33,166
Larry, they gave
us an AS we missed.

1025
00:54:33,270 --> 00:54:35,410
Joe, what if this
million-to-one,

1026
00:54:35,513 --> 00:54:39,103
snowball's chance in hell,
when pigs have wings looser tip

