00:56:38,153 --> 00:56:39,292
What's going on, Adam?

1076
00:56:39,396 --> 00:56:41,708
It's a police investigation.

1077
00:56:41,812 --> 00:56:43,814
Got to ask questions.

1078
00:56:43,917 --> 00:56:45,332
I worked with Terry.

1079
00:56:45,436 --> 00:56:48,197
But were you here that night?

1080
00:56:48,301 --> 00:56:50,683
Well, where else would I be?

1081
00:56:50,786 --> 00:56:53,479
You're almost never
here at night, Adam.

1082
00:56:53,582 --> 00:56:55,619
What-- what, am I lying now?

1083
00:56:55,722 --> 00:56:56,792
YVONNE: No, I didn't say that.

1084
00:56:56,896 --> 00:57:00,417
Well, Yvonne, you don't
sound that confident.

1085
00:57:00,520 --> 00:57:02,798
I just think that you're
not telling me something.

1086
00:57:05,732 --> 00:57:09,426
Well, then you
think too damn much.

1087
00:57:09,529 --> 00:57:10,634
Don't be mad, Adam.

1088
00:57:10,737 --> 00:57:11,876
I hate it when
you get mad at me.

1089
00:57:11,980 --> 00:57:13,084
Please?
- Please!

1090
00:57:13,188 --> 00:57:13,947
Adam.

1091
00:57:14,051 --> 00:57:15,362
What?

1092
00:57:15,466 --> 00:57:16,260
What?

1093
00:57:16,363 --> 00:57:18,400
You make me mad.

1094
00:57:18,504 --> 00:57:19,436
Oh, and there.

1095
00:57:19,539 --> 00:57:20,678
And now you don't like it.

1096
00:57:25,303 --> 00:57:26,995
Come here, come here.

1097
00:57:27,098 --> 00:57:27,996
Come here.

1098
00:57:34,243 --> 00:57:35,037
Look at you.

1099
00:57:35,141 --> 00:57:36,556
You're as big as a house.

1100
00:57:36,660 --> 00:57:37,454
Thanks.

1101
00:57:37,557 --> 00:57:38,351
Come here.

1102
00:57:38,455 --> 00:57:39,559
Listen.

1103
00:57:39,663 --> 00:57:42,355
You know that I'm going to
take care of you, right?

1104
00:57:42,459 --> 00:57:46,532
You know that I'm
always there for you.

1105
00:57:46,635 --> 00:57:49,017
Right?

1106
00:57:49,120 --> 00:57:54,022
Well, I expect the mother
of my child to stand by me.

1107
00:57:54,125 --> 00:57:56,369
Huh?

1108
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:57,853
I can't hear you, Yvonne.

1109
00:57:57,957 --> 00:58:00,200
Right, Adam.

1110
00:58:00,304 --> 00:58:01,270
All right.

1111
00:58:05,999 --> 00:58:07,587
Renee didn't tell you
she's been suspended?

1112
00:58:07,691 --> 00:58:08,864
She didn't mention it.

1113
00:58:08,968 --> 00:58:09,762
What was the reason?

1114
00:58:09,865 --> 00:58:11,073
She slapped Adam Schuster.

1115
00:58:11,177 --> 00:58:12,454
The woman's completely unstable.

1116
00:58:12,558 --> 00:58:13,455
Nate!

1117
00:58:15,733 --> 00:58:17,977
Did either of you ever
notice any problem between Adam

1118
00:58:18,080 --> 00:58:19,081
Schuster and Terry Deveroux?

1119
00:58:19,185 --> 00:58:20,324
Well, absolutely not.

1120
00:58:20,427 --> 00:58:21,670
Adam is no murderer.

1121
00:58:21,774 --> 00:58:22,809
That's great.
Fine.

1122
00:58:22,913 --> 00:58:24,259
Thanks, Deanna.

1123
00:58:24,362 --> 00:58:25,605
You know his
girlfriend's expecting?

1124
00:58:25,709 --> 00:58:27,607
The guy is working
overtime just to provide

1125
00:58:27,711 --> 00:58:28,608
for her and the baby.

1126
00:58:28,712 --> 00:58:30,161
He's even moonlighting.
- Oh, yeah?

1127
00:58:30,265 --> 00:58:31,059
What's he doing?

1128
00:58:31,162 --> 00:58:32,405
NATE: Electronics.

1129
00:58:32,509 --> 00:58:34,649
He put himself through night
school, repairs TVs, VCRs,

1130
00:58:34,752 --> 00:58:37,583
stuff like that.

1131
00:58:37,686 --> 00:58:39,550
So the voodoo
lady is ticked off

1132
00:58:39,654 --> 00:58:42,380
at Schuster for some damn
reason and gets him arrested.

1133
00:58:42,484 --> 00:58:44,279
But why is she ticked
off in the first place?

1134
00:58:44,382 --> 00:58:46,315
Because the ghost told
her he was the killer?

1135
00:58:46,419 --> 00:58:47,558
Oh, come on, Joe.

1136
00:58:47,662 --> 00:58:50,009
You know that Terry
Deveroux's TV was on the fritz.

1137
00:58:50,112 --> 00:58:52,149
What am I missing here?

1138
00:58:52,252 --> 00:58:54,772
The guy said Schuster's been
moonlighting as a TV repairman.

1139
00:58:54,876 --> 00:58:57,741
Maybe that puts him
in her apartment.

1140
00:58:57,844 --> 00:58:58,880
Now that's what
I call a stretch.

1141
00:58:58,983 --> 00:59:00,709
[scoffs] Maybe.

1142
00:59:00,813 --> 00:59:01,779
So?

1143
00:59:01,883 --> 00:59:02,815
No, no, no, no.

1144
00:59:02,918 --> 00:59:06,335
This is-- take this
to 307, all right?

1145
00:59:06,439 --> 00:59:07,923
Hey, we need to talk.

1146
00:59:08,027 --> 00:59:08,855
Yeah, what's up?

1147
00:59:08,959 --> 00:59:09,753
It's Renee.

1148
00:59:09,856 --> 00:59:10,685
She's at it again.

1149
00:59:10,788 --> 00:59:12,065
She contacted the police.

1150
00:59:12,169 --> 00:59:14,585
She told them that you
killed Terry Deveroux.

1151
00:59:14,689 --> 00:59:15,828
What?

1152
00:59:15,931 --> 00:59:18,624
They were just here, talking
to me and Donna Larson.

1153
00:59:18,727 --> 00:59:20,142
What did you guys say to them?

1154
00:59:20,246 --> 00:59:22,006
She's nuts.

1155
00:59:22,110 --> 00:59:24,699
I can't believe that
she called the police.

1156
00:59:24,802 --> 00:59:28,254
She is out to nail you.

1157
00:59:28,357 --> 00:59:32,292
[suspenseful music]

1158
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:49,171
[gasps and screams]

1159
00:59:49,275 --> 00:59:50,483
- Hey, come here!
- No!

1160
00:59:50,587 --> 00:59:51,726
- Let me move you.
- Let me go!

1161
00:59:51,829 --> 00:59:52,761
No, not yet.

1162
00:59:52,865 --> 00:59:53,659
[screams]

1163
00:59:53,762 --> 00:59:54,867
Hey, hey, hey!

1164
00:59:54,970 --> 00:59:56,593
Hey, shut up, shut up.

1165
00:59:56,696 --> 00:59:58,560
Shut up, all right?

1166
00:59:58,664 --> 00:59:59,768
Shut up.

1167
00:59:59,872 --> 01:00:00,873
OK?

1168
01:00:00,976 --> 01:00:01,770
All right?

1169
01:00:01,874 --> 01:00:03,185
Mhm.

1170
01:00:03,289 --> 01:00:04,670
- All right.
- These--

1171
01:00:04,773 --> 01:00:06,188
No, Renee, Renee,
Renee, listen, listen.

1172
01:00:06,292 --> 01:00:07,431
Focus on the business, OK?

1173
01:00:07,534 --> 01:00:09,985
Now, you created this
problem for yourself.

1174
01:00:10,089 --> 01:00:11,090
You came after me, and now look.

1175
01:00:11,193 --> 01:00:12,022
You see?

1176
01:00:12,125 --> 01:00:13,333
Here I am, right?

1177
01:00:13,437 --> 01:00:15,439
Now, what I want
you to tell me is

1178
01:00:15,542 --> 01:00:16,543
just what you told the police.

1179
01:00:16,647 --> 01:00:18,545
That's all.

1180
01:00:18,649 --> 01:00:21,583
What did you say to them, Renee?

1181
01:00:21,687 --> 01:00:24,137
What you did to Terry.

1182
01:00:24,241 --> 01:00:26,243
Where did you get that from?

1183
01:00:26,346 --> 01:00:27,140
Talk to me.

1184
01:00:27,244 --> 01:00:29,764
She told me.

1185
01:00:29,867 --> 01:00:31,282
What?

1186
01:00:31,386 --> 01:00:32,629
Terry told me.

1187
01:00:38,669 --> 01:00:41,189
You are crazy.

1188
01:00:41,292 --> 01:00:42,259
Yeah, well, that's they think.

1189
01:00:42,362 --> 01:00:43,363
So you don't have to worry.

1190
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:48,748
Listen to me.

1191
01:00:48,852 --> 01:00:52,165
From now on, you keep
your mouth shut about me.

1192
01:00:52,269 --> 01:00:53,201
All right?

1193
01:00:53,304 --> 01:00:54,202
Mhm.

1194
01:01:00,139 --> 01:01:01,071
I'll see ya.

1195
01:01:22,748 --> 01:01:24,611
Renee?

1196
01:01:24,715 --> 01:01:25,612
You there?

1197
01:01:30,790 --> 01:01:34,207
[radio static]

1198
01:01:48,774 --> 01:01:49,671
Renee.

1199
01:02:00,509 --> 01:02:03,305
Why won't the police
arrest Adam Schuster?

1200
01:02:03,409 --> 01:02:06,550
Please, go away.

1201
01:02:06,653 --> 01:02:08,000
Can't you see what
you're doing to her?

1202
01:02:08,103 --> 01:02:09,380
She can't take any more of this.

1203
01:02:09,484 --> 01:02:12,383
Renee wants to help me.

1204
01:02:12,487 --> 01:02:14,213
Why won't you?

1205
01:02:14,316 --> 01:02:15,455
We tried.

1206
01:02:15,559 --> 01:02:17,216
No one believes us.

1207
01:02:17,319 --> 01:02:19,080
Don't you understand?

1208
01:02:19,183 --> 01:02:23,049
It's not our fault.
No one believes us.

1209
01:02:23,153 --> 01:02:26,397
I have evidence.

1210
01:02:26,501 --> 01:02:28,675
Go to the police.

1211
01:02:28,779 --> 01:02:31,644
Tell them he stole my jewelry
and gave it to the girl.

1212
01:02:39,445 --> 01:02:41,516
The voodoo lady to see you.

1213
01:02:41,619 --> 01:02:43,207
[laughs]

1214
01:02:43,311 --> 01:02:44,208
Excuse me.

1215
01:02:48,799 --> 01:02:50,559
Mrs. Perkins, how can I help?

1216
01:02:50,663 --> 01:02:52,113
Adam Schuster
broke into my house.

1217
01:02:52,216 --> 01:02:53,562
I was alone, and
he threatened me.

1218
01:02:53,666 --> 01:02:54,771
Sorry, Mrs. Perkins.

1219
01:02:54,874 --> 01:02:56,220
If you file a complaint,
we'll be more than happy--

1220
01:02:56,324 --> 01:02:58,395
I want you to arrest him
for killing Terry Deveroux.

1221
01:02:58,498 --> 01:03:00,466
We can't build a
case on what we've got.

1222
01:03:00,569 --> 01:03:03,296
I can give you proof.

1223
01:03:03,400 --> 01:03:04,815
Adam stole some
jewelry from Terry,

1224
01:03:04,919 --> 01:03:06,437
and he gave it to
his girlfriend;

1225
01:03:06,541 --> 01:03:09,302
a sapphire ring,
some gold earrings,

1226
01:03:09,406 --> 01:03:12,305
and an art deco style black
onyx pin with diamond gems.

1227
01:03:12,409 --> 01:03:13,755
This information
about the jewelry,

1228
01:03:13,859 --> 01:03:15,861
did this come to
you in a vision too?

1229
01:03:15,964 --> 01:03:16,827
Does it matter?

1230
01:03:22,764 --> 01:03:25,940
Look, I believed you when
you told me how badly you

1231
01:03:26,043 --> 01:03:27,700
want to catch Terry's killer.

1232
01:03:27,804 --> 01:03:29,426
I still do.

1233
01:03:29,529 --> 01:03:31,428
That's why I'm sure you're going
to follow through with this,

1234
01:03:31,531 --> 01:03:34,638
no matter how crazy it seems.

1235
01:03:34,741 --> 01:03:37,434
Do you really want to wonder
for the rest of your life

1236
01:03:37,537 --> 01:03:39,954
if you had it in your
hands, by some miracle,

1237
01:03:40,057 --> 01:03:43,785
to do the right thing
and you just let it go?

1238
01:03:50,343 --> 01:03:53,243
[knocks on door]

1239
01:03:58,593 --> 01:03:59,525
Good afternoon.

1240
01:03:59,628 --> 01:04:00,698
I was wondering if
you had some time

1241
01:04:00,802 --> 01:04:02,355
to come to the station
with us and answer

1242
01:04:02,459 --> 01:04:03,978
a few more questions?

1243
01:04:04,081 --> 01:04:04,910
Am I under arrest?

1244
01:04:05,013 --> 01:04:06,049
Absolutely not.

1245
01:04:06,152 --> 01:04:06,981
OK.

1246
01:04:07,084 --> 01:04:08,051
Step in.

1247
01:04:08,154 --> 01:04:09,500
Yvonne?
YVONNE: What?

1248
01:04:09,604 --> 01:04:10,743
I'm going to go
down to the station.

1249
01:04:10,847 --> 01:04:14,609
I'm going to help out
the detectives here.

1250
01:04:14,712 --> 01:04:15,852
I'll be back soon, OK?

1251
01:04:15,955 --> 01:04:16,853
Uh, OK.

1252
01:04:20,373 --> 01:04:21,512
Where's your other guy?

1253
01:04:21,616 --> 01:04:23,480
Oh, he's going to ask
Yvonne a couple of questions.

1254
01:04:26,138 --> 01:04:27,001
Why don't we go ahead?

1255
01:04:31,177 --> 01:04:33,559
Did you need something?

1256
01:04:33,662 --> 01:04:37,114
As a matter of fact, yes.

1257
01:04:37,218 --> 01:04:39,910
I wanted to ask you if Adam had
given you any jewelry recently.

1258
01:04:45,122 --> 01:04:48,091
Um, am-- am I going
to be in trouble?

1259
01:04:51,646 --> 01:04:52,785
Listen.

1260
01:04:52,889 --> 01:04:55,719
I hardly knew Terry
Deveroux, all right?

1261
01:04:55,822 --> 01:04:57,755
The problem is I have
different information.

1262
01:04:57,859 --> 01:04:58,722
Huh.

1263
01:04:58,825 --> 01:04:59,965
We have a neighbor
that says he saw

1264
01:05:00,068 --> 01:05:01,449
you around Terry's apartment.

1265
01:05:01,552 --> 01:05:03,106
Oh, yeah, six
months ago, maybe.

1266
01:05:03,209 --> 01:05:05,418
Six months ago, I might have
bumped into her on the street,

1267
01:05:05,522 --> 01:05:07,420
helped her bring some groceries
upstairs or something,

1268
01:05:07,524 --> 01:05:08,697
you know?

1269
01:05:08,801 --> 01:05:09,906
Well, if it was
six months ago,

1270
01:05:10,009 --> 01:05:11,597
there'd be no reason to
find your prints there.

1271
01:05:14,393 --> 01:05:16,602
Tell you what we're going to do.

1272
01:05:16,705 --> 01:05:17,879
I'm going to take
some fingerprints,

1273
01:05:17,983 --> 01:05:19,329
see if they match up
with the set of prints

1274
01:05:19,432 --> 01:05:20,571
we found in her apartment.

1275
01:05:20,675 --> 01:05:21,469
Yeah, fine.

1276
01:05:21,572 --> 01:05:22,435
That's good.

1277
01:05:22,539 --> 01:05:23,505
You should do what
you have to do.

1278
01:05:23,609 --> 01:05:24,506
We will.

1279
01:05:28,303 --> 01:05:30,029
Tell me about your
TV repair business.

1280
01:05:34,068 --> 01:05:36,277
Terry Deveroux's TV
was out of order.

1281
01:05:36,380 --> 01:05:37,209
Come on, Adam.

1282
01:05:37,312 --> 01:05:39,452
We know about your moonlighting.

1283
01:05:39,556 --> 01:05:41,351
Oh, OK.

1284
01:05:41,454 --> 01:05:43,111
Um, let me think.

1285
01:05:43,215 --> 01:05:45,424
Um, oh, right.

1286
01:05:45,527 --> 01:05:46,735
I see.

1287
01:05:46,839 --> 01:05:48,841
Yes, I think I might have
been there more recently.

1288
01:05:48,945 --> 01:05:51,223
I was going to fix
her television set,

1289
01:05:51,326 --> 01:05:53,052
and she was going to
give me some comedy

1290
01:05:53,156 --> 01:05:54,433
club tickets instead of paying.

1291
01:05:54,536 --> 01:05:56,469
That's right.

1292
01:05:56,573 --> 01:05:58,333
Was that around April 23?

1293
01:05:58,437 --> 01:05:59,507
Uh, yeah.

1294
01:05:59,610 --> 01:06:01,164
[clears throat] Yep.

1295
01:06:01,267 --> 01:06:03,304
What happened when
you went to fix her TV?

1296
01:06:03,407 --> 01:06:05,789
Well, I didn't have the
right part, and so I left.

1297
01:06:05,892 --> 01:06:08,619
And then, I forgot all about
it, and I never came back.

1298
01:06:08,723 --> 01:06:10,173
And that is the god's truth.

1299
01:06:14,694 --> 01:06:15,764
Who told you
about her jewelry?

1300
01:06:18,284 --> 01:06:19,182
I don't--

1301
01:06:19,285 --> 01:06:20,252
I don't know anything
about jewelry.

1302
01:06:20,355 --> 01:06:21,149
Sure, you do.

1303
01:06:21,253 --> 01:06:23,186
[chuckles] I don't.

1304
01:06:23,289 --> 01:06:25,912
Try to remember.

1305
01:06:26,016 --> 01:06:28,018
You got a minute, Joe?

1306
01:06:28,122 --> 01:06:30,745
You got Yvonne waiting.

1307
01:06:30,848 --> 01:06:33,230
Got to leave you for
a few minutes, Adam.

1308
01:06:33,334 --> 01:06:34,300
You got Yvonne--

1309
01:06:34,404 --> 01:06:37,027
what's-- what do you
got Yvonne here for?

1310
01:06:37,131 --> 01:06:39,133
We think she's material
to the investigation,

1311
01:06:39,236 --> 01:06:40,962
but don't you worry about that.

1312
01:06:44,103 --> 01:06:45,346
We'll take good care of her.

1313
01:06:45,449 --> 01:06:49,177
We're highly respectful of
expectant mothers around here.

1314
01:06:49,281 --> 01:06:50,523
You need anything?

1315
01:06:50,627 --> 01:06:51,524
Huh?

1316
01:06:51,628 --> 01:06:52,974
JOE: Cup of coffee?

1317
01:06:53,078 --> 01:06:53,837
No, nothing.

1318
01:06:53,940 --> 01:06:54,734
No, I'm fine.

1319
01:06:54,838 --> 01:06:56,219
Can I talk to Yvonne?

1320
01:06:56,322 --> 01:06:57,185
Maybe later.

1321
01:07:00,292 --> 01:07:02,259
He admitted to being in
Terry Deveroux's apartment

1322
01:07:02,363 --> 01:07:04,123
the night of the murder.

1323
01:07:04,227 --> 01:07:05,400
Oh, he's waiting for us.

1324
01:07:07,644 --> 01:07:08,472
Hi, Jeff.

1325
01:07:08,576 --> 01:07:09,508
I'm glad you could make it.

1326
01:07:09,611 --> 01:07:10,405
Thanks for coming down.

1327
01:07:10,509 --> 01:07:11,579
Sure thing.

1328
01:07:11,682 --> 01:07:12,580
You ready?

1329
01:07:12,683 --> 01:07:13,581
Yeah.

1330
01:07:16,273 --> 01:07:19,794
Yvonne, this is Jeff
Deveroux, a relative

1331
01:07:19,897 --> 01:07:22,003
of the victim, Terry Deveroux.

1332
01:07:22,107 --> 01:07:23,142
Hello.

1333
01:07:23,246 --> 01:07:24,385
I'm very sorry about your loss.

1334
01:07:24,488 --> 01:07:25,386
Thank you.

1335
01:07:28,527 --> 01:07:30,115
Ma'am, forgive me for
asking, but why are you

1336
01:07:30,218 --> 01:07:31,357
wearing my cousin's earrings?

1337
01:07:36,949 --> 01:07:38,640
The ring, that's Terry's too.

1338
01:07:48,133 --> 01:07:49,030
Terry's.

1339
01:07:58,488 --> 01:08:00,662
I'm so sorry.

1340
01:08:00,766 --> 01:08:01,663
I didn't know.

1341
01:08:18,853 --> 01:08:20,234
It's all over, Adam.

1342
01:08:20,337 --> 01:08:21,821
One of Terry Deveroux's
family members

1343
01:08:21,925 --> 01:08:25,239
identified the jewelry
box that you gave Yvonne.

1344
01:08:25,342 --> 01:08:27,379
Two pair of earrings.

1345
01:08:27,482 --> 01:08:28,656
Sapphire ring.

1346
01:08:28,759 --> 01:08:31,176
Well, I bought that jewelry
from a guy on the street.

1347
01:08:31,279 --> 01:08:32,694
You have a receipt, Adam?

1348
01:08:32,798 --> 01:08:33,626
Well, no.

1349
01:08:33,730 --> 01:08:34,593
They don't give receipts.

1350
01:08:34,696 --> 01:08:35,525
Hey, come on now.

1351
01:08:35,628 --> 01:08:36,595
You're pushing it, Adam.

1352
01:08:36,698 --> 01:08:38,321
You lied about being
in her apartment.

1353
01:08:38,424 --> 01:08:39,977
You lied about the
night of the 23rd.

1354
01:08:40,081 --> 01:08:41,565
Which Yvonne corroborated.
Am I right, Joe?

1355
01:08:41,669 --> 01:08:42,808
That's right.

1356
01:08:42,911 --> 01:08:44,672
Which could make her an
accessory after the fact.

1357
01:08:44,775 --> 01:08:48,400
I think it would be pretty sad
to have a baby born in lockup.

1358
01:08:48,503 --> 01:08:49,401
Hey, you--

1359
01:08:53,715 --> 01:08:54,613
Hey, Yvonne is--

1360
01:08:58,064 --> 01:08:59,549
[sighs]

1361
01:09:05,037 --> 01:09:06,487
She didn't know
anything about it.

1362
01:09:06,590 --> 01:09:07,798
About what, Adam?

1363
01:09:07,902 --> 01:09:09,524
Terry Deveroux's murder?

1364
01:09:09,628 --> 01:09:10,525
Yeah.

1365
01:09:10,629 --> 01:09:12,562
Are you ready to
talk about it, Adam?

1366
01:09:12,665 --> 01:09:13,563
Yeah.

1367
01:09:26,852 --> 01:09:28,440
I killed her.

1368
01:09:28,543 --> 01:09:30,373
Why did you kill her?

1369
01:09:30,476 --> 01:09:31,857
I got a kid on the way.

1370
01:09:31,960 --> 01:09:34,411
I needed the money.

1371
01:09:34,515 --> 01:09:37,345
I was going to rob her.

1372
01:09:37,449 --> 01:09:39,899
Hey, everybody knew that
she came from money.

1373
01:09:40,003 --> 01:09:40,900
She was loaded.

1374
01:09:48,391 --> 01:09:50,220
So I go to her place.

1375
01:09:50,324 --> 01:09:51,946
She wasn't going to let me in.

1376
01:09:52,049 --> 01:09:54,328
I guess I wasn't
convenient, like,

1377
01:09:54,431 --> 01:09:56,330
what, I'm some kind
of servant, I guess.

1378
01:09:56,433 --> 01:09:59,436
She's better than me.

1379
01:09:59,540 --> 01:10:01,852
Anyway, I talked her into it.

1380
01:10:01,956 --> 01:10:02,853
She let me in.

1381
01:10:05,994 --> 01:10:08,687
You know, she's standing there
in her expensive dress, and--

1382
01:10:11,517 --> 01:10:12,311
whatever.

1383
01:10:12,415 --> 01:10:13,830
I got a kid on the way.

1384
01:10:19,284 --> 01:10:21,424
I didn't rape her.

1385
01:10:21,527 --> 01:10:22,425
Yeah.

1386
01:10:27,430 --> 01:10:28,914
That's, uh--
that's great news.

1387
01:10:29,017 --> 01:10:30,605
Congratulations.

1388
01:10:30,709 --> 01:10:31,537
Yeah, yeah.

1389
01:10:31,641 --> 01:10:32,573
And thanks a lot.

1390
01:10:32,676 --> 01:10:33,470
You too.

1391
01:10:33,574 --> 01:10:34,920
Bye.

1392
01:10:35,023 --> 01:10:35,817
It's over.

1393
01:10:35,921 --> 01:10:37,336
Schuster confessed.

1394
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:38,337
Thank god!

1395
01:10:42,099 --> 01:10:43,584
We were told there
wouldn't be a trial.

1396
01:10:43,687 --> 01:10:44,964
Adam Schuster
would be sentenced,

1397
01:10:45,068 --> 01:10:46,863
and that would be it.

1398
01:10:46,966 --> 01:10:48,589
Renee was asked back
to work, but decided

1399
01:10:48,692 --> 01:10:49,728
to take a little more time off.

1400
01:10:49,831 --> 01:10:52,800
And I focused on
finishing my residency.

1401
01:10:52,903 --> 01:10:54,871
We had done what
Terry wanted, and we

1402
01:10:54,974 --> 01:10:57,356
thought it was all behind us.

1403
01:10:57,460 --> 01:10:59,185
I need to talk to
you two for a minute.

1404
01:10:59,289 --> 01:11:00,186
Hey, Mr. Prosecutor.

1405
01:11:00,290 --> 01:11:01,187
How's it going?

1406
01:11:01,291 --> 01:11:02,499
Schuster just
withdrew his confession.

1407
01:11:02,603 --> 01:11:03,638
Damn!

1408
01:11:03,742 --> 01:11:06,745
You want to tell me
about this, detective?

1409
01:11:06,848 --> 01:11:07,849
Not a welcome surprise.

1410
01:11:07,953 --> 01:11:09,265
I don't think you
have to worry about it.

1411
01:11:09,368 --> 01:11:10,404
It's just a memo.

1412
01:11:10,507 --> 01:11:12,060
You think the defense
won't see through that?

1413
01:11:12,164 --> 01:11:13,407
They'll accuse you
of trying to hide it,

1414
01:11:13,510 --> 01:11:14,891
and I can't help but
think they'll be right.

1415
01:11:14,994 --> 01:11:16,651
Hey, O'Gane, we
handed you a confession.

1416
01:11:16,755 --> 01:11:18,239
This case is a slam dunk.

1417
01:11:18,343 --> 01:11:20,345
We have some serious
probable cause issues.

1418
01:11:20,448 --> 01:11:22,554
You can't make an arrest based
on this kind of information.

1419
01:11:22,657 --> 01:11:23,520
JOE: We know that.

1420
01:11:23,624 --> 01:11:25,108
All we did was bring
him in to talk.

1421
01:11:25,211 --> 01:11:26,696
He was arrested
after he confessed.

1422
01:11:26,799 --> 01:11:28,387
This, along with all
the other paperwork,

1423
01:11:28,491 --> 01:11:30,251
was just subpoenaed
by the defense.

1424
01:11:30,355 --> 01:11:31,908
It's part of the
official record now.

1425
01:11:32,011 --> 01:11:33,219
That's how it came
across my desk.

1426
01:11:33,323 --> 01:11:34,773
Otherwise, I probably
would never have seen it.

1427
01:11:34,876 --> 01:11:36,015
Am I right, detective?

1428
01:11:36,119 --> 01:11:36,982
You were trying to hide it.

1429
01:11:37,085 --> 01:11:38,294
Not really.

1430
01:11:38,397 --> 01:11:39,743
[SCOFFING] Not really.

1431
01:11:39,847 --> 01:11:42,574
Well, now I have to prove to a
jury beyond a reasonable doubt

1432
01:11:42,677 --> 01:11:45,680
that, uh, Renee
Perkins was possessed

1433
01:11:45,784 --> 01:11:47,199
by the spirit of the victim.

1434
01:11:47,303 --> 01:11:49,788
They made it perfectly clear
they want to be kept out of it.

1435
01:11:49,891 --> 01:11:51,237
Oh, yeah?

1436
01:11:51,341 --> 01:11:52,238
Tell that to the defense.

1437
01:11:58,693 --> 01:11:59,694
Evening, detective.

1438
01:11:59,798 --> 01:12:01,317
Nice to see you.
- Nice seeing you.

1439
01:12:01,420 --> 01:12:02,145
Thanks.
How are you?

1440
01:12:02,248 --> 01:12:03,146
[phone ringing]
BILL: Hey.

1441
01:12:03,249 --> 01:12:04,216
Yeah, we were--
- Hello?

1442
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:06,977
BILL: --kind of surprised
when you called.

1443
01:12:07,081 --> 01:12:07,944
Who is this?

1444
01:12:08,047 --> 01:12:09,428
BILL: What brings you out here?

1445
01:12:09,532 --> 01:12:10,326
You could say--

1446
01:12:10,429 --> 01:12:11,430
RENEE: How did
you get my number?

1447
01:12:11,534 --> 01:12:14,226
No, I don't-- I
don't have a comment.

1448
01:12:14,330 --> 01:12:17,781
Detective, that was a reporter.

1449
01:12:17,885 --> 01:12:22,303
Could I comment on my role in
the case against Adam Schuster?

1450
01:12:22,407 --> 01:12:24,892
He said Schuster's
recanting his confession.

1451
01:12:24,995 --> 01:12:26,549
He's claiming he was coerced.

1452
01:12:26,652 --> 01:12:27,481
His lawyers got to him.

1453
01:12:27,584 --> 01:12:28,654
I know this has
been tough on you,

1454
01:12:28,758 --> 01:12:30,587
and they're probably
going to ask you--

1455
01:12:30,691 --> 01:12:32,140
well, you can expect a subpoena.

1456
01:12:32,244 --> 01:12:33,556
You're going to have to testify.

1457
01:12:33,659 --> 01:12:35,627
Oh, boy.

1458
01:12:35,730 --> 01:12:37,870
Oh, Bill.

1459
01:12:37,974 --> 01:12:38,871
I'm so sorry.

1460
01:12:45,395 --> 01:12:46,396
[knocking on door]

1461
01:12:46,500 --> 01:12:47,363
Come in.

1462
01:12:49,986 --> 01:12:51,021
Hi, Dr. Carter.

1463
01:12:51,125 --> 01:12:51,919
Hello, Bill.

1464
01:12:52,022 --> 01:12:52,920
Have a seat.

1465
01:12:57,925 --> 01:13:00,306
I called you here today
because of my respect for you

1466
01:13:00,410 --> 01:13:03,206
as a doctor.

1467
01:13:03,309 --> 01:13:05,691
I wanted to let
you know personally

1468
01:13:05,795 --> 01:13:07,900
we've decided to go
with another candidate

1469
01:13:08,004 --> 01:13:08,936
for the staff position.

1470
01:13:12,318 --> 01:13:13,216
I see.

1471
01:13:31,303 --> 01:13:32,822
REPORTER: I think that's
him, I think that's him.

1472
01:13:32,925 --> 01:13:34,548
Oh, oh, get a shot of him
coming up the driveway!

1473
01:13:34,651 --> 01:13:35,411
Come on.
Let's go.

1474
01:13:35,514 --> 01:13:36,273
Stay with me.
Come on.

1475
01:13:36,377 --> 01:13:37,171
Uh, Dr. Perkins?

1476
01:13:37,274 --> 01:13:38,793
- Dr. Perkins?
- Dr. Perkins?

1477
01:13:38,897 --> 01:13:40,105
Dr. Perkins?

1478
01:13:40,208 --> 01:13:41,244
Dr. Perkins, has your wife
had any visions concerning

1479
01:13:41,347 --> 01:13:42,487
the outcome of the trial?

1480
01:13:42,590 --> 01:13:44,489
Do you belong to any
religious cults, Dr. Perkins?

1481
01:13:44,592 --> 01:13:45,593
REPORTER: What about your wife?
I mean, is she feeling OK?

1482
01:13:45,697 --> 01:13:46,732
Has she ever tried any
hallucinogenic drugs?

1483
01:13:46,836 --> 01:13:49,804
[reporters clamoring]

1484
01:13:51,323 --> 01:13:52,980
Have you got any
comment at all for us?

1485
01:13:53,083 --> 01:13:54,637
BILL: Get a life.

1486
01:13:54,740 --> 01:13:55,638
[phone ringing]

1487
01:13:55,741 --> 01:13:57,674
Can you believe these people?

1488
01:13:57,778 --> 01:13:59,055
I'll get it.
- No.

1489
01:13:59,158 --> 01:14:00,366
Honey, no.

1490
01:14:00,470 --> 01:14:04,060
It's probably just a crackpot
or reporter, or both.

1491
01:14:04,163 --> 01:14:06,959
Didn't get the job.

1492
01:14:07,063 --> 01:14:09,168
Oh, Bill.

1493
01:14:09,272 --> 01:14:11,170
Carter was a
gentleman about it.

1494
01:14:11,274 --> 01:14:13,241
At least I didn't get a
form letter in the mail.

1495
01:14:13,345 --> 01:14:15,071
It's because of me.

1496
01:14:15,174 --> 01:14:17,591
Ah, it's the trial.

1497
01:14:17,694 --> 01:14:18,557
I'm so sorry.

1498
01:14:25,875 --> 01:14:28,671
Renee, the defense is
going to use your testimony

1499
01:14:28,774 --> 01:14:31,328
to try and get the jury's
mind off the real issue

1500
01:14:31,432 --> 01:14:34,504
of the record, which is the
fact that Schuster confessed.

1501
01:14:34,608 --> 01:14:38,819
One thing I absolutely have
to know without ambiguity,

1502
01:14:38,922 --> 01:14:41,511
do you plan on
sticking by your story?

1503
01:14:41,615 --> 01:14:44,928
Only if they still require
the truth, Mr. O'Gane.

1504
01:14:45,032 --> 01:14:45,929
That's all I need to know.

1505
01:14:53,799 --> 01:14:56,664
Mr. Schuster, could
you tell the jury

1506
01:14:56,768 --> 01:14:58,424
how you knew Terry
Deveroux had not

1507
01:14:58,528 --> 01:15:01,048
been raped when the police did
not release that information?

1508
01:15:01,151 --> 01:15:02,325
Uh, I didn't know that.

1509
01:15:02,428 --> 01:15:04,327
But you said in
your confession,

1510
01:15:04,430 --> 01:15:09,159
and I quote, "I just wanted
to make it look like a rape.

1511
01:15:09,263 --> 01:15:11,265
That's why I moved
her legs apart."

1512
01:15:11,368 --> 01:15:13,543
Oh, well, the
detectives there, they--

1513
01:15:13,647 --> 01:15:16,650
they wrote that confession,
and I just signed that.

1514
01:15:16,753 --> 01:15:18,617
So your testimony is
now that you've lied

1515
01:15:18,721 --> 01:15:19,860
when you made this statement?

1516
01:15:19,963 --> 01:15:21,896
Uh, well, the--

1517
01:15:22,000 --> 01:15:23,277
the detectives
threatened me, sir.

1518
01:15:23,380 --> 01:15:24,934
They told me that if I
didn't sign the confession--

1519
01:15:25,037 --> 01:15:27,764
Mr. Schuster.

1520
01:15:27,868 --> 01:15:29,628
You answered my question.

1521
01:15:29,732 --> 01:15:30,595
OK, sorry.

1522
01:15:34,771 --> 01:15:36,566
Mr. Smith?

1523
01:15:36,670 --> 01:15:40,881
Adam, will you
tell the jury, why

1524
01:15:40,984 --> 01:15:43,608
did you confess to the
murder of Terry Deveroux

1525
01:15:43,711 --> 01:15:45,264
if you're an innocent man?

1526
01:15:45,368 --> 01:15:49,855
Well, Yvonne, she was
about to have our first baby.

1527
01:15:49,959 --> 01:15:54,135
And the detective said
that she would be arrested,

1528
01:15:54,239 --> 01:15:57,242
and that our baby would
be born in jail if I

1529
01:15:57,345 --> 01:15:59,969
didn't sign that confession.

1530
01:16:00,072 --> 01:16:03,213
So you were forced to
sign a false confession?

1531
01:16:03,317 --> 01:16:05,664
That's the way
I felt. Yes, sir.

1532
01:16:05,768 --> 01:16:08,149
You know, I would have confessed
to killing Kennedy or whatever

1533
01:16:08,253 --> 01:16:10,186
if they would have promised
to leave Yvonne and the baby

1534
01:16:10,289 --> 01:16:11,843
alone.

1535
01:16:11,946 --> 01:16:13,879
Thank you,

1536
01:16:13,983 --> 01:16:15,191
You may step down.

1537
01:16:15,294 --> 01:16:16,192
Thanks.

1538
01:16:18,228 --> 01:16:19,989
Detective, would
you tell the jury

1539
01:16:20,092 --> 01:16:23,199
what happens to evidence seized
or arrests made in the absence

1540
01:16:23,302 --> 01:16:24,821
of probable cause?

1541
01:16:24,925 --> 01:16:26,029
It becomes invalidated.

1542
01:16:26,133 --> 01:16:26,961
I'm sorry?

1543
01:16:27,065 --> 01:16:29,412
I didn't hear you.

1544
01:16:29,515 --> 01:16:30,689
It becomes invalidated.

1545
01:16:30,793 --> 01:16:32,070
ATTORNEY SMITH:
Detective Stachula,

1546
01:16:32,173 --> 01:16:34,728
was Adam Schuster a suspect in
the murder of Terry Deveroux

1547
01:16:34,831 --> 01:16:37,800
before Renee Perkins told
you her story of having

1548
01:16:37,903 --> 01:16:39,387
visions and being possessed?

1549
01:16:39,491 --> 01:16:41,527
No, he was not
a suspect until I

1550
01:16:41,631 --> 01:16:43,426
got a tip that he
was in possession

1551
01:16:43,529 --> 01:16:44,841
of the victim's jewelry.

1552
01:16:44,945 --> 01:16:47,050
ATTORNEY SMITH: Well,
that's very good, Detective,

1553
01:16:47,154 --> 01:16:48,604
but would you be
good enough to tell

1554
01:16:48,707 --> 01:16:51,399
us where that tip came from?

1555
01:16:51,503 --> 01:16:52,366
Renee Perkins.

1556
01:16:52,469 --> 01:16:53,678
ATTORNEY SMITH: And
did Mrs. Perkins

1557
01:16:53,781 --> 01:16:55,887
say that that information
came from Terry Deveroux?

1558
01:16:55,990 --> 01:16:56,991
Yes, she did.

1559
01:16:57,095 --> 01:16:58,165
ATTORNEY SMITH: And
Terry Deveroux's been

1560
01:16:58,268 --> 01:17:00,305
dead for, what, four weeks now?

1561
01:17:00,408 --> 01:17:01,720
JOE: Yes, that's true.

1562
01:17:01,824 --> 01:17:03,757
ATTORNEY SMITH: I'd like to
direct your attention to a copy

1563
01:17:03,860 --> 01:17:07,968
of Exhibit C, a memo from you
to your supervisor, Captain

1564
01:17:08,071 --> 01:17:08,969
Kirkwood.

1565
01:17:13,629 --> 01:17:14,699
You did write that memo?

1566
01:17:14,802 --> 01:17:16,045
JOE: Yes, I did.

1567
01:17:16,148 --> 01:17:18,288
And it describes your first
meeting with Renee Perkins.

1568
01:17:18,392 --> 01:17:19,738
Is that right?

1569
01:17:19,842 --> 01:17:21,015
Yes, it does.

1570
01:17:21,119 --> 01:17:23,880
ATTORNEY SMITH: Allow me
to read the first sentence.

1571
01:17:23,984 --> 01:17:27,366
And I quote, "you aren't
going to believe this."

1572
01:17:30,715 --> 01:17:34,477
Detective Stachula, do
you believe in ghosts?

1573
01:17:34,580 --> 01:17:36,065
[scoffs]

1574
01:17:39,620 --> 01:17:43,244
Now, Mr. Bradshaw, you've
worked with both the defendant

1575
01:17:43,348 --> 01:17:45,143
and Renee Perkins
for over two years.

1576
01:17:45,246 --> 01:17:47,283
You know them pretty well.

1577
01:17:47,386 --> 01:17:50,044
Do you believe Adam Schuster
provoked this incident?

1578
01:17:50,148 --> 01:17:51,080
Oh, no.

1579
01:17:51,183 --> 01:17:53,599
I was shocked when
she slapped Adam.

1580
01:17:53,703 --> 01:17:55,809
They've always
worked well together,

1581
01:17:55,912 --> 01:17:59,122
that is until her miscarriage.

1582
01:17:59,226 --> 01:18:00,745
Maybe she was just jealous--

1583
01:18:00,848 --> 01:18:02,678
O'Gane was right.

1584
01:18:02,781 --> 01:18:03,713
I'm the one on trial.

1585
01:18:08,235 --> 01:18:11,825
Mr. O'Gane, how do
you think it's going?

1586
01:18:11,928 --> 01:18:13,619
Stachula's testimony
hurt, didn't it?

1587
01:18:13,723 --> 01:18:14,724
Mhm.

1588
01:18:14,828 --> 01:18:17,658
And our real Achilles'
heel is yet to come.

1589
01:18:17,762 --> 01:18:19,039
Meaning me, of course.

1590
01:18:19,142 --> 01:18:20,316
I'm afraid so.

1591
